WEBVTT

00:00:00.180 --> 00:00:04.360
So, ladies and gentlemen, we move on

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:10.110
to the study of macroeconomics.

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:14.740
See topic 5 on the slide.

00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:17.140
Macroeconomic aggregates are

00:00:17.150 --> 00:00:19.820
a large domestic product.

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:21.800
Well, let's first remember

00:00:21.810 --> 00:00:26.800
again what macroeconomics actually studies.

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:31.500
Microeconomics – what is it studying?

00:00:32.220 --> 00:00:34.860
The behavior of individual economic

00:00:34.870 --> 00:00:38.140
agents and their interaction in individual

00:00:38.150 --> 00:00:39.880
markets.

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:43.560
Macroeconomics studies the

00:00:43.570 --> 00:00:46.820
economy as a whole.

00:00:48.780 --> 00:00:51.920
And the most important methodological

00:00:51.930 --> 00:00:53.980
feature of macroeconomics

00:00:53.990 --> 00:00:59.240
is aggregation, that is, generalization.

00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:03.020
The macroeconomic view of the

00:01:03.030 --> 00:01:07.140
national economy distinguishes four

00:01:07.150 --> 00:01:14.780
generalized economic subjects.

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:17.680
This, look at the slide, first

00:01:17.690 --> 00:01:19.320
of all, households.

00:01:20.260 --> 00:01:22.180
These are all private economic

00:01:22.190 --> 00:01:24.860
units within the country whose

00:01:24.870 --> 00:01:26.560
activities are aimed

00:01:26.570 --> 00:01:28.700
at meeting their own needs.

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:33.180
Further, macroeconomics distinguishes

00:01:33.190 --> 00:01:35.580
the entrepreneurial sector, that

00:01:35.590 --> 00:01:37.740
is, the whole set of firms

00:01:37.750 --> 00:01:40.140
registered within the country.

00:01:41.990 --> 00:01:43.490
The next macroeconomic aggregate

00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:46.910
is the public sector.

00:01:47.310 --> 00:01:49.250
It includes all state institutions

00:01:49.260 --> 00:01:51.370
and institutions of the country.

00:01:52.290 --> 00:01:55.830
And finally, the fourth aggregate is

00:01:55.840 --> 00:01:57.190
the overseas.

00:01:57.190 --> 00:02:00.290
Foreign includes all economic

00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:02.550
entities – both households,

00:02:02.560 --> 00:02:04.650
firms, and foreign states,

00:02:04.660 --> 00:02:06.590
that is, all entities

00:02:06.600 --> 00:02:09.610
that have a permanent location

00:02:09.620 --> 00:02:11.830
outside the country.

00:02:11.840 --> 00:02:13.230


00:02:15.510 --> 00:02:17.850
That is, four large

00:02:17.860 --> 00:02:19.910
aggregated economic agents

00:02:19.920 --> 00:02:22.550
operate in the macroeconomy

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:25.690
– households, firms, the

00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:27.630
state, abroad.

00:02:30.850 --> 00:02:33.330
Macroeconomic aggregation

00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:35.850
extends to markets.

00:02:36.350 --> 00:02:38.390
The macroeconomic view distinguishes

00:02:38.400 --> 00:02:43.870
four aggregated markets.

00:02:44.470 --> 00:02:48.270
It is the commodity market, labour market,

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:52.030
money market and securities market.

00:02:53.930 --> 00:02:56.470
Note that in macroeconomics

00:02:56.480 --> 00:03:00.590
there is no market for

00:03:00.600 --> 00:03:02.830
separate goods, separate

00:03:02.840 --> 00:03:03.870
goods.

00:03:04.090 --> 00:03:06.770
There is no oil market, wheat

00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:09.310
market, or gold market.

00:03:11.990 --> 00:03:15.250
In macroeconomics, there is a single market

00:03:15.260 --> 00:03:19.170
that unites all the benefits.

00:03:19.250 --> 00:03:22.390
In this market, the total

00:03:22.400 --> 00:03:26.630
volume, the total volume, the national

00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:28.870
production, the social production,

00:03:29.090 --> 00:03:30.470
the domestic product

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:33.690
are sold and bought.

00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:40.590
Let's talk about the domestic product.

00:03:42.110 --> 00:03:43.670
The domestic product is the

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:46.010
market value of all

00:03:46.020 --> 00:03:48.670
goods and services intended

00:03:48.850 --> 00:03:50.350
for final consumption

00:03:50.360 --> 00:03:53.150
and produced in the country

00:03:53.160 --> 00:03:55.850
over a certain period

00:03:55.860 --> 00:03:56.770
of time.

00:04:01.190 --> 00:04:04.410
If, to imagine a domestic

00:04:06.860 --> 00:04:10.250
product, it is best to imagine

00:04:10.260 --> 00:04:14.230
the economy in the form of a

00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:16.010
giant supermarket.

00:04:17.450 --> 00:04:21.030
This supermarket exhibits all goods

00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:25.250
and services produced over a certain

00:04:25.260 --> 00:04:27.650
period of time in the territory

00:04:27.660 --> 00:04:30.430
of the country.

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:33.870
All goods and services are intended

00:04:33.880 --> 00:04:36.370
for final consumption.

00:04:36.750 --> 00:04:39.830
Here in this corner, for example, nuclear

00:04:39.840 --> 00:04:42.450
submarines, in this corner, bakeries,

00:04:42.460 --> 00:04:45.270
there costumes, here cars, there

00:04:45.280 --> 00:04:47.650
are the services of doctors, teachers

00:04:47.670 --> 00:04:49.390
and artists.

00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:52.850
The whole set of goods and services

00:04:52.860 --> 00:04:54.550
intended for final consumption

00:04:54.560 --> 00:04:57.290
forms the domestic

00:04:57.300 --> 00:04:58.950
product.

00:04:59.710 --> 00:05:02.730
I want to draw your attention to the fact

00:05:05.380 --> 00:05:10.450
that the domestic product includes

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:14.450
cars, but does not include steel, does

00:05:14.460 --> 00:05:17.010
not include metal, which went to

00:05:17.020 --> 00:05:19.030
the production of cars.

00:05:19.510 --> 00:05:20.870
The domestic product of the

00:05:20.880 --> 00:05:22.730
wool consists of goods

00:05:22.870 --> 00:05:25.330
intended for final consumption.

00:05:25.710 --> 00:05:27.370
Products intended for intermediate

00:05:27.380 --> 00:05:29.830
consumption are not included

00:05:29.840 --> 00:05:33.550
in the wool domestic product.

00:05:33.810 --> 00:05:35.470
There are cars, but no

00:05:35.480 --> 00:05:36.630
metal.

00:05:36.690 --> 00:05:39.710
Dresses are included, but no wool is included,

00:05:39.720 --> 00:05:41.550
no fabric is included.

00:05:43.330 --> 00:05:46.230
Includes gasoline if it

00:05:46.240 --> 00:05:50.650
is sold if it is sold to car enthusiasts.

00:05:51.070 --> 00:05:53.610
It is considered the final product.

00:05:53.620 --> 00:05:56.830
But the price of oil in the domestic

00:05:56.840 --> 00:05:58.810
product is not included.

00:05:59.470 --> 00:06:02.150
Oil is the raw material for the production of gasoline.

00:06:02.370 --> 00:06:04.190
Gasoline is in, but there is no oil.

00:06:05.410 --> 00:06:08.450
The only necessary reservation.

00:06:09.610 --> 00:06:13.270
The price of oil is taken into

00:06:13.280 --> 00:06:15.250
account when calculating the

00:06:15.260 --> 00:06:18.490
domestic product if oil goes

00:06:18.500 --> 00:06:19.850
for export.

00:06:19.860 --> 00:06:24.870
Oil is the final product

00:06:24.880 --> 00:06:28.850
of our economy.

00:06:30.790 --> 00:06:34.030
The problem now is how to measure

00:06:34.040 --> 00:06:39.870
GDP – the domestic product.

00:06:40.170 --> 00:06:44.330
There are three ways to measure GDP.

00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:49.600
To better understand these ways, let'

00:06:50.260 --> 00:06:52.140
s go back to my conditional example

00:06:52.150 --> 00:06:53.920
with the supermarket.

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:57.940
This conditional supermarket

00:06:57.950 --> 00:07:01.260
exhibits all goods and services

00:07:01.480 --> 00:07:03.300
intended for final consumption

00:07:03.310 --> 00:07:07.140
and produced in the

00:07:07.150 --> 00:07:08.840
country.

00:07:10.400 --> 00:07:13.220
How can we find out the value of this

00:07:13.230 --> 00:07:14.060
total GDP?

00:07:15.160 --> 00:07:17.800
Well, the easiest way is to circumvent

00:07:17.810 --> 00:07:20.160
all the shelves, rewrite

00:07:20.540 --> 00:07:23.000
prices, multiply by volumes,

00:07:23.010 --> 00:07:24.720
and then fold.

00:07:24.840 --> 00:07:29.780
This means that we measure

00:07:29.790 --> 00:07:32.200
GDP by cost of production

00:07:32.210 --> 00:07:34.380
or production methods.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:38.100
See, the first way to

00:07:38.110 --> 00:07:41.300
measure GDP by cost of production.

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:45.240
How can we measure?

00:07:47.890 --> 00:07:51.470
We assume that if a product is

00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:55.050
produced, it will be bought by someone

00:07:55.060 --> 00:07:55.730
else.

00:07:56.990 --> 00:08:00.430
If a product is produced but not yet purchased,

00:08:00.440 --> 00:08:02.410
here is a small statistical

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:05.450
nuance of its accounting when calculating

00:08:05.460 --> 00:08:06.750
GDP.

00:08:07.050 --> 00:08:08.870
But let's first assume that everything

00:08:09.170 --> 00:08:12.470
that is produced is bought by someone.

00:08:12.710 --> 00:08:15.030
How can we measure

00:08:15.040 --> 00:08:16.050
GDP?

00:08:17.430 --> 00:08:19.970
You can, conditionally speaking, after

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:23.930
the end of the trading day to remove the cash.

00:08:26.020 --> 00:08:28.300
If a product is purchased by someone,

00:08:28.310 --> 00:08:30.700
the value of the product

00:08:30.710 --> 00:08:33.660
is equal to the sum of the

00:08:33.670 --> 00:08:35.960
costs of all consumers.

00:08:37.160 --> 00:08:41.560
The second way to measure GDP is

00:08:41.570 --> 00:08:45.380
by the sum of all consumer expenses.

00:08:46.140 --> 00:08:48.140
This method of measuring

00:08:48.150 --> 00:08:51.560
GDP is called the end-use method.

00:08:51.570 --> 00:08:56.400
The third method is based on the

00:08:56.410 --> 00:09:01.100
sum of primary income or the sum of the

00:09:01.110 --> 00:09:04.260
income of all the participants in production.

00:09:04.980 --> 00:09:06.820
This is called the

00:09:06.830 --> 00:09:09.000
distribution method.

00:09:10.340 --> 00:09:12.140
What is this method based on?

00:09:12.640 --> 00:09:15.500
It is based on the fact that

00:09:15.510 --> 00:09:18.160
if consumers paid some amount of

00:09:18.170 --> 00:09:20.680
money, the product they bought,

00:09:20.690 --> 00:09:25.840
that money did not disappear.

00:09:26.160 --> 00:09:29.940
They became the income of those who participated

00:09:29.950 --> 00:09:32.100
in the production process.

00:09:37.090 --> 00:09:40.350
Well, look, let's give an example

00:09:40.360 --> 00:09:43.330
so that you can, maybe, better

00:09:43.340 --> 00:09:44.470
understand it.

00:09:49.930 --> 00:09:55.090
You bought this audio course.

00:09:59.580 --> 00:10:05.620
It is printed in a 100 copy printing.

00:10:06.900 --> 00:10:08.960
Each copy, let's say, costs

00:10:09.220 --> 00:10:11.940
100 rubles.

00:10:14.210 --> 00:10:18.070
How can this rate contribute to

00:10:18.080 --> 00:10:20.450
the GDP of Russia?

00:10:21.650 --> 00:10:23.230
Can be calculated how.

00:10:24.030 --> 00:10:28.250
10 copies or 100 copies.

00:10:28.550 --> 00:10:31.610
Each copy costs 100 rubles.

00:10:32.090 --> 00:10:34.250
This is the final product.

00:10:34.590 --> 00:10:36.730
The cost, cost, total cost

00:10:36.740 --> 00:10:40.050
is 10 thousand rubles.

00:10:42.710 --> 00:10:43.710
This is the first way.

00:10:43.850 --> 00:10:47.610
GDP is measured by production method.

00:10:49.010 --> 00:10:49.990
and further.

00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:52.850
Someone bought this course.

00:10:53.830 --> 00:10:54.790
Can I do anything?

00:10:55.510 --> 00:10:58.590
Put all the costs, all buyers

00:10:58.600 --> 00:11:01.410
on this, to purchase this

00:11:01.420 --> 00:11:02.490
course.

00:11:02.670 --> 00:11:04.690
It will be the same 10,000 rubles.

00:11:06.310 --> 00:11:07.310
And then what?

00:11:08.410 --> 00:11:10.630
If you paid for this course,

00:11:10.640 --> 00:11:15.930
someone got that money.

00:11:16.150 --> 00:11:18.050
Who was who got?

00:11:18.830 --> 00:11:20.030
For example, I am.

00:11:20.630 --> 00:11:21.670
Who else?

00:11:22.470 --> 00:11:25.170
All those who have participated

00:11:25.180 --> 00:11:27.230
in this course.

00:11:27.410 --> 00:11:30.150
So your course expenses

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:31.330
turned into what?

00:11:32.530 --> 00:11:36.270
The income of those who participated in its creation.

00:11:36.870 --> 00:11:39.430
Here it turns out that GDP can be measured

00:11:39.440 --> 00:11:41.390
once again in the patria in three ways.

00:11:41.790 --> 00:11:43.630
The first way how?

00:11:43.970 --> 00:11:45.170
by cost of production.

00:11:45.370 --> 00:11:49.190
The second is the total cost of all consumers.

00:11:49.450 --> 00:11:52.050
The third method, by the sum of the

00:11:52.060 --> 00:11:54.310
income of all producers involved in its

00:11:54.320 --> 00:11:56.930
creation, in the creation of this product.

00:11:57.590 --> 00:11:59.990
If we use all three methods correctly,

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:04.030
they should give the same

00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:04.530
result.

00:12:05.570 --> 00:12:11.830
In this painting I tried to

00:12:13.340 --> 00:12:17.870
paint the same thing, paint

00:12:17.880 --> 00:12:19.090
the same thing.

00:12:19.950 --> 00:12:21.350
What is in the center?

00:12:22.790 --> 00:12:25.430
The domestic product.

00:12:26.150 --> 00:12:29.550
This is the value of all final

00:12:29.560 --> 00:12:32.510
goods and services produced

00:12:32.520 --> 00:12:34.070
in the country.

00:12:35.590 --> 00:12:37.830
What is on the left?

00:12:38.210 --> 00:12:40.070
expenses of all consumers.

00:12:41.770 --> 00:12:45.330
In macroeconomics, we distinguish

00:12:45.340 --> 00:12:47.570
four main groups of consumers.

00:12:48.650 --> 00:12:50.890
Who buys our goods?

00:12:51.710 --> 00:12:54.550
Who is, in our case, in the

00:12:54.560 --> 00:12:57.810
rows in our supermarket?

00:12:59.430 --> 00:13:02.290
Who is on one side?

00:13:02.870 --> 00:13:05.650
households buying goods

00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:07.310
for personal use.

00:13:08.390 --> 00:13:10.590
Who is on the other side?

00:13:11.590 --> 00:13:14.610
Companies that buy goods for

00:13:14.620 --> 00:13:16.050
production consumption.

00:13:17.230 --> 00:13:18.870
End products for production

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:20.230
consumption are machines,

00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:22.550
machines, equipment,

00:13:22.730 --> 00:13:25.270
buildings, structures.

00:13:25.280 --> 00:13:28.430
The cost will also be included in GDP.

00:13:28.610 --> 00:13:31.110
Who else is in our supermarket?

00:13:32.530 --> 00:13:34.170
State officials.

00:13:34.510 --> 00:13:37.330
They buy goods

00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:38.750
for the state.

00:13:39.510 --> 00:13:41.110
And finally, the last group

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:45.390
of buyers, who are you, see below?

00:13:45.530 --> 00:13:46.430
The Foreigners.

00:13:46.810 --> 00:13:49.470
Foreigners we buy and understand everyone.

00:13:49.730 --> 00:13:52.370
Foreign firms, foreign

00:13:52.380 --> 00:13:54.030
governments, and foreign

00:13:54.040 --> 00:13:54.990
households.

00:14:00.590 --> 00:14:02.530
Is the value of GDP

00:14:02.540 --> 00:14:06.550
equal to what?

00:14:06.830 --> 00:14:09.650
Costs of all consumers.

00:14:09.810 --> 00:14:11.550
I repeat, states, households,

00:14:11.790 --> 00:14:14.390
firms and foreigners.

00:14:15.750 --> 00:14:17.670
What happens next?

00:14:18.310 --> 00:14:22.110
The arrows are right in the revenue direction.

00:14:22.870 --> 00:14:27.330
This means that the expenses of some

00:14:27.340 --> 00:14:30.210
have become the income of others.

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:38.680
When the GDP is sold, who gets

00:14:38.690 --> 00:14:39.540
their share?

00:14:42.010 --> 00:14:45.310
Employees in the form of pay.

00:14:51.220 --> 00:14:53.860
Capitalists receive a percentage on the

00:14:53.870 --> 00:14:55.860
invested capital.

00:14:58.230 --> 00:15:01.070
Shareholders receive dividends.

00:15:01.470 --> 00:15:04.610
Land owners receive rent.

00:15:05.070 --> 00:15:08.110
Entrepreneurs are making profits.

00:15:08.330 --> 00:15:11.210
These are the main types of income.

00:15:11.250 --> 00:15:13.550
This figure is intended

00:15:13.560 --> 00:15:14.850
to make it clear that the sum,

00:15:14.860 --> 00:15:17.790
the cost of production, is

00:15:17.800 --> 00:15:21.110
equal to the sum of costs.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:23.330
What is produced, who is bought.

00:15:23.610 --> 00:15:27.610
The expenses are turned into whose income.

00:15:28.050 --> 00:15:30.730
We see here the four main groups

00:15:30.740 --> 00:15:34.010
of buyers and the main types

00:15:34.020 --> 00:15:36.450
of income in the market economy.

00:15:37.230 --> 00:15:42.970
Now here is an important nuance.

00:15:44.590 --> 00:15:51.210
In the 92nd year, Russia'

00:15:51.220 --> 00:15:55.150
s GDP was about 640 billion rubles.

00:15:58.870 --> 00:16:02.610
By 2007, it would be

00:16:02.620 --> 00:16:07.050
more than 27 trillion rubles.

00:16:09.990 --> 00:16:15.810
Does this mean that GDP has grown somewhere

00:16:15.820 --> 00:16:20.670
47 times over that period?

00:16:25.380 --> 00:16:28.460
What is the real social production

00:16:28.470 --> 00:16:31.520
increased by 47 times?

00:16:32.560 --> 00:16:33.680
Absolutely not.

00:16:34.460 --> 00:16:38.220
GDP cannot be measured in pieces,

00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:41.340
in tons, in meters of

00:16:41.350 --> 00:16:42.460
vehicles.

00:16:43.220 --> 00:16:47.440
GDP can be measured in rubles.

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:51.940
The tables are different.

00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:53.820
They can be brought to a single

00:16:53.830 --> 00:16:56.120
denominator only by means of

00:16:56.130 --> 00:16:57.540
a ruble measurement.

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:02.720
And if so, the size of GDP is influenced,

00:17:02.730 --> 00:17:07.920
on the one hand, by the change in the

00:17:07.930 --> 00:17:10.560
physical volumes of products produced,

00:17:10.570 --> 00:17:13.900
and on the other hand by the change

00:17:13.910 --> 00:17:15.740
in prices.

00:17:19.220 --> 00:17:22.280
There is a distinction between

00:17:22.290 --> 00:17:26.840
nominal and real GDP.

00:17:27.280 --> 00:17:29.820
We read the definition on the slide.

00:17:31.810 --> 00:17:36.870
Nominal GDP is GDP calculated

00:17:37.130 --> 00:17:40.730
in current prices.

00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:46.820
And when I say that Russia's

00:17:46.830 --> 00:17:50.360
GDP in 1992 was 640 billion

00:17:52.150 --> 00:17:54.880
rubles, and now it will soon

00:17:54.890 --> 00:17:58.520
exceed 27 trillion rubles,

00:17:58.530 --> 00:18:01.360
I am speaking precisely of

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:04.680
a change in nominal GDP.

00:18:07.510 --> 00:18:11.230
Why is nominal GDP changing?

00:18:11.250 --> 00:18:13.130
influenced by two factors.

00:18:14.690 --> 00:18:16.970
The first factor is the change

00:18:16.980 --> 00:18:18.830
in physical production volumes.

00:18:19.650 --> 00:18:22.290
The second factor is price change.

