we can use this theory to analyze

00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:54.150
how the real GDP changes

00:31:54.160 --> 00:31:56.250
in the Russian economy.

00:31:58.470 --> 00:32:02.210
The State Statistics Service publishes

00:32:02.220 --> 00:32:04.850
data on the change in nominal GDP by year.

00:32:07.390 --> 00:32:09.190
What can we do?

00:32:09.490 --> 00:32:13.410
Let's say we are interested in how

00:32:13.420 --> 00:32:18.110
much real GDP grew or fell in 2007.

00:32:19.490 --> 00:32:21.750
We have to wait for nominal

00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:26.750
GDP data in 2006 and 2007.

00:32:27.670 --> 00:32:33.530
Divide the nominal GDP of 2007 by

00:32:35.410 --> 00:32:40.240
the nominal GDP of 2006.

00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:42.200
What will we get?

00:32:43.880 --> 00:32:46.300
The nominal GDP index.

00:32:48.390 --> 00:32:52.690
Then we need to find data on price

00:32:52.700 --> 00:32:57.750
changes for this year.

00:33:00.810 --> 00:33:04.570
The price index used to link

00:33:04.580 --> 00:33:06.190
nominal and real GDP

00:33:06.200 --> 00:33:08.970
is called the deflator

00:33:08.980 --> 00:33:11.370
of GDP.

00:33:13.740 --> 00:33:18.620
If we find a deflator of GDP, what

00:33:18.630 --> 00:33:19.680
can we do?

00:33:21.020 --> 00:33:23.760
The nominal GDP index is divided by

00:33:23.770 --> 00:33:26.960
this price index or deflator of GDP.

00:33:26.970 --> 00:33:31.200
This is the real GDP

00:33:31.210 --> 00:33:33.720
index.

00:33:34.120 --> 00:33:38.860
Suppose it was 1.07.

00:33:40.060 --> 00:33:41.820
What does this mean?

00:33:43.720 --> 00:33:49.440
That real GDP for 2007 increased

00:33:49.450 --> 00:33:55.500
by 1.07 times or 7%.

00:33:57.920 --> 00:34:01.080
In addition to GDP, there are a

00:34:01.090 --> 00:34:04.840
number of macroeconomic indicators.

00:34:05.780 --> 00:34:06.960
Let us talk about them.

00:34:12.770 --> 00:34:16.930
First of all, we distinguish between

00:34:16.940 --> 00:34:20.730
the domestic product and the

00:34:20.740 --> 00:34:22.130
national income.

00:34:26.440 --> 00:34:29.300
Look at the slide.

00:34:29.580 --> 00:34:35.440
GDP is the product produced in

00:34:35.450 --> 00:34:38.920
the country by both residents

00:34:38.930 --> 00:34:42.300
and non-residents.

00:34:43.120 --> 00:34:46.020
Residents are considered persons, not

00:34:46.030 --> 00:34:48.200
necessarily citizens of a country, but

00:34:48.210 --> 00:34:51.060
those who have, as they say, the center

00:34:51.070 --> 00:34:52.960
of economic interest in the territory

00:34:52.970 --> 00:34:54.380
of that country.

00:34:54.390 --> 00:34:57.400
You can not be a citizen, but a resident.

00:34:59.270 --> 00:35:01.570
GNI (Bill National Income) is the sum of

00:35:01.580 --> 00:35:05.850
primary income received by residents

00:35:05.990 --> 00:35:08.050
of a given country as a result of

00:35:08.060 --> 00:35:11.170
their participation in the creation of

00:35:11.180 --> 00:35:14.770
GDP of that country, as well as GDP of

00:35:14.780 --> 00:35:16.190
other countries.

00:35:19.020 --> 00:35:20.800
Let us give an example.

00:35:23.450 --> 00:35:27.990
Let's say that Russians work abroad.

00:35:28.630 --> 00:35:31.830
They are therefore involved in creating the GDP

00:35:31.840 --> 00:35:33.230
of other countries.

00:35:34.950 --> 00:35:37.930
But by participating in its creation,

00:35:37.940 --> 00:35:40.950
they get some income.

00:35:41.990 --> 00:35:45.770
Their income is the income of Russian

00:35:45.780 --> 00:35:49.690
residents, although received abroad.

00:35:49.850 --> 00:35:53.470
Their income is part of the

00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:57.270
Russian national income.

00:35:57.910 --> 00:36:04.820
On the other hand, if, say, an American

00:36:08.230 --> 00:36:10.550
resident works in Russia, he participates

00:36:10.560 --> 00:36:14.830
in the creation of Russia'

00:36:14.840 --> 00:36:15.970
s GDP.

00:36:18.360 --> 00:36:20.780
The income will be included in the GDP

00:36:20.790 --> 00:36:21.760
of Russia.

00:36:23.280 --> 00:36:24.780
But at the same time, it is the income

00:36:24.790 --> 00:36:26.920
of the American resident, so it will enter

00:36:26.930 --> 00:36:29.440
the VAT, the wave of the national

00:36:29.450 --> 00:36:30.360
income of the United States.

00:36:32.780 --> 00:36:37.900
Look at the slide formula.

00:36:38.080 --> 00:36:41.280
GNI is equal to the national

00:36:41.290 --> 00:36:45.200
income, GDP plus the balance

00:36:45.210 --> 00:36:48.600
of primary income received from

00:36:48.610 --> 00:36:52.760
abroad or transferred abroad.

00:36:52.770 --> 00:36:58.630
Let us take a look at this example

00:36:58.640 --> 00:36:59.590
with you.

00:37:04.590 --> 00:37:08.550
Let the foreigners not participate

00:37:08.560 --> 00:37:11.050
in the Russian economy by their

00:37:11.060 --> 00:37:13.170
labor, their capital, or anything.

00:37:13.180 --> 00:37:13.630


00:37:14.370 --> 00:37:18.310
Russians work abroad.

00:37:20.160 --> 00:37:23.400
The GDP of Russia was 100

00:37:23.410 --> 00:37:24.280
rubles.

00:37:28.710 --> 00:37:32.430
In addition, the Russians earned

00:37:32.440 --> 00:37:34.410
10 rubles abroad.

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:43.600
GDP is 100.

00:37:44.540 --> 00:37:47.620
In addition to the income received by Russians

00:37:47.630 --> 00:37:48.980
abroad, there are 10 more.

00:37:49.640 --> 00:37:53.140
The GNV is 110.

00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:55.780
GDP, the largest institutional income

00:37:55.790 --> 00:37:59.520
of Russia, exceeded its GDP.

00:37:59.800 --> 00:38:02.800
The reverse example.

00:38:03.800 --> 00:38:05.920
Suppose the Russians are not

00:38:05.930 --> 00:38:08.320
in any way involved in creating

00:38:08.330 --> 00:38:09.540
foreign GDP.

00:38:11.720 --> 00:38:15.320
Foreigners are contributing

00:38:15.330 --> 00:38:17.880
their capital to the Russian GDP.

00:38:20.650 --> 00:38:25.400
GDP of Russia is 100 rubles.

00:38:26.300 --> 00:38:29.360
But, let's say, of these 100 rubles,

00:38:29.370 --> 00:38:32.820
5 rubles is the income

00:38:32.830 --> 00:38:34.920
of foreign residents.

00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:40.140
Therefore, in order to calculate the GNI of

00:38:40.150 --> 00:38:46.460
Russia, these 5 rubles must be deducted from the GDP.

00:38:48.460 --> 00:38:51.320
100 rubles of the total GDP of Russia, including

00:38:51.330 --> 00:38:54.200
5 rubles, is the contribution of

00:38:54.210 --> 00:38:56.480
foreigners to the creation of our GDP.

00:38:58.440 --> 00:39:00.560
The gross national income of Russia,

00:39:00.570 --> 00:39:04.360
the Russians, is 95.

00:39:05.240 --> 00:39:08.060
And if there are both, that is, we are

00:39:08.070 --> 00:39:09.380
participating in creating

00:39:09.390 --> 00:39:12.520
foreign GDP, foreigners are

00:39:12.530 --> 00:39:15.220
participating in creating our GDP,

00:39:15.400 --> 00:39:16.280
what should we do?

00:39:17.620 --> 00:39:21.540
It is necessary to add to GDP the

00:39:21.550 --> 00:39:24.500
balance of income received from abroad

00:39:24.510 --> 00:39:27.560
