In this regard, we distinguish four

00:58:15.410 --> 00:58:17.640
groups of consumers.

00:58:18.600 --> 00:58:20.780
The first group of consumers

00:58:20.790 --> 00:58:26.080
are households, families, individuals.

00:58:26.640 --> 00:58:29.780
The second group of consumers are companies.

00:58:31.060 --> 00:58:34.680
The third group is the state.

00:58:35.620 --> 00:58:37.900
The fourth group is foreigners.

00:58:39.180 --> 00:58:41.900
Accordingly, the total demand, read

00:58:42.400 --> 00:58:46.020
on the slide, is broken down into,

00:58:48.880 --> 00:58:51.260
first, the costs of private

00:58:51.270 --> 00:58:56.280
consumers, marked by the letter C.

00:58:56.290 --> 00:58:59.880
Consumption is consumer expenses.

00:59:00.540 --> 00:59:04.080
On the other hand, companies, if

00:59:04.090 --> 00:59:06.440
you remember, buy machines, machines,

00:59:06.600 --> 00:59:07.880
equipment, and so on.

00:59:08.720 --> 00:59:10.080
This is called investment

00:59:10.090 --> 00:59:12.420
demand.

00:59:12.440 --> 00:59:14.800
The second part of the total

00:59:14.810 --> 00:59:16.680
demand is the investment

00:59:16.690 --> 00:59:18.860
costs of the companies.

00:59:20.940 --> 00:59:24.400
The third is the expenses of the state.

00:59:24.960 --> 00:59:27.240
The fourth part is foreign

00:59:27.250 --> 00:59:30.380
expense or net export.

00:59:31.440 --> 00:59:34.280
And if you look at the aggregate demand

00:59:34.290 --> 00:59:37.320
from this perspective, the equation

00:59:37.330 --> 00:59:39.580
of aggregate demand takes

00:59:39.590 --> 00:59:40.820
shape.

00:59:41.040 --> 00:59:43.020
Look at the slide.

00:59:43.080 --> 00:59:48.120
Y is C plus I plus G plus X N.

00:59:51.370 --> 00:59:53.050
What comes from here?

00:59:55.860 --> 00:59:58.900
The increase of any of these

00:59:58.910 --> 01:00:01.580
components of aggregate demand at a given

01:00:01.590 --> 01:00:05.180
price level leads to the fact that the

01:00:05.920 --> 01:00:08.740
curve A and D, the curve of

01:00:08.750 --> 01:00:12.380
aggregate demand, shifts to the right.

01:00:12.480 --> 01:00:13.780
And the opposite.

01:00:14.120 --> 01:00:15.840
The decrease of any of these components

01:00:17.590 --> 01:00:19.900
of the aggregate demand at the same time,

01:00:19.910 --> 01:00:22.580
at the unchanged level of prices, entails

01:00:23.060 --> 01:00:25.620
a shift of the aggregate demand

01:00:25.630 --> 01:00:27.920
curve to the left.

01:00:28.020 --> 01:00:30.660
That is, the overall demand is decreasing.

01:00:31.460 --> 01:00:33.780
Well, this is actually shown on the slide,

01:00:33.790 --> 01:00:36.500
which you have already looked at a little

01:00:36.510 --> 01:00:37.280
earlier.

01:00:37.640 --> 01:00:39.040
We can see it again,

01:00:39.050 --> 01:00:41.360
on the same slide.

01:00:46.350 --> 01:00:49.570
Curve A, D can shift to the right or to

01:00:49.580 --> 01:00:50.690
the left.

