Now, let's talk about the fourth

01:02:38.370 --> 01:02:41.830
factor, consumer expectations.

01:02:42.810 --> 01:02:46.290
Remember, we talked about expectations,

01:02:46.310 --> 01:02:48.230
again, in the microeconomy, in the

01:02:48.240 --> 01:02:49.830
model of supply and demand.

01:02:52.950 --> 01:02:54.890
What expectations were there?

01:02:58.560 --> 01:03:01.520
If you remember, about the expectations

01:03:01.530 --> 01:03:05.500
of price changes of goods.

01:03:07.840 --> 01:03:10.520
That is, if people expect that the

01:03:10.530 --> 01:03:12.880
product will be more expensive,

01:03:12.890 --> 01:03:15.840
they will buy it at the same price, usually

01:03:18.100 --> 01:03:20.490
at the current price.

01:03:22.680 --> 01:03:25.100
In macroeconomics, we also talk about

01:03:25.110 --> 01:03:28.340
