Accordingly, if the interest rate

01:05:02.480 --> 01:05:06.190
is high, then we will most likely

01:05:06.200 --> 01:05:09.050
take less money out of loan.

01:05:09.060 --> 01:05:10.790
So less and spend.

01:05:11.710 --> 01:05:13.670
That is, at a high interest

01:05:13.680 --> 01:05:15.750
rate, the household's consumer

01:05:15.760 --> 01:05:16.970
expenses will be less.

01:05:17.510 --> 01:05:18.510
And lowly the opposite.

