01:06:14.340 --> 01:06:16.940
But above all, here I would like

01:06:18.570 --> 01:06:21.820
to emphasize that in macroeconomics

01:06:23.020 --> 01:06:26.660
we share the nominal interest

01:06:26.670 --> 01:06:30.640
rate and the real interest rate.

01:06:33.210 --> 01:06:34.890
The nominal interest rate, look

01:06:34.900 --> 01:06:38.550
at the slide, is the rate at

01:06:38.870 --> 01:06:41.150
which a loan agreement is

01:06:41.160 --> 01:06:42.850
concluded, at which

01:06:42.860 --> 01:06:44.950
funds are borrowed on the financial

01:06:44.960 --> 01:06:46.310
markets.

01:06:48.990 --> 01:06:51.930
The real interest rate is a change

01:06:51.940 --> 01:06:53.950
in the purchasing power

01:06:53.960 --> 01:06:57.350
of interest income.

01:06:57.450 --> 01:07:00.190
The relationship between nominal and

01:07:00.200 --> 01:07:02.810
real interest rates is determined

01:07:02.820 --> 01:07:05.910
by the Fisher equation.

01:07:06.570 --> 01:07:09.350
It's very simple, look at the slide.

01:07:09.490 --> 01:07:12.490
The real interest rate is equal to the

01:07:12.500 --> 01:07:14.950
nominal interest rate minus the

01:07:14.960 --> 01:07:17.390
rate of inflation.

01:07:20.840 --> 01:07:23.400
Let us give the simplest example.

01:07:24.860 --> 01:07:29.780
The loan contract is under 10% of the annual.

01:07:32.300 --> 01:07:35.320
This is the nominal interest rate.

01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:39.780
At the same time, during the year, prices

01:07:39.790 --> 01:07:43.220
increased by 4%.

01:07:44.480 --> 01:07:46.340
I think we will come to a situation

01:07:46.350 --> 01:07:47.560
when we have inflation

01:07:47.570 --> 01:07:50.500
not above 4% a year.

01:07:50.860 --> 01:07:51.820
This is still considered to be a

01:07:51.830 --> 01:07:54.680
lot of the standards of developed economies.

01:07:54.880 --> 01:07:55.580
Well well well.

01:07:55.880 --> 01:07:58.260
Let it be 4%.

01:07:58.270 --> 01:07:59.420
What does this mean?

01:07:59.540 --> 01:08:02.060
10% minus 4%.

01:08:02.070 --> 01:08:05.940
The real interest rate is 6%.

01:08:05.950 --> 01:08:09.880
This is the percentage that the lender

01:08:09.890 --> 01:08:12.460
actually receives from the money

01:08:12.470 --> 01:08:13.960
borrowed.

01:08:15.300 --> 01:08:18.220
Dependence is not difficult.

01:08:18.580 --> 01:08:21.400
The lower the real interest rate,

01:08:21.410 --> 01:08:24.640
the higher the investment costs of the

01:08:24.650 --> 01:08:26.000
companies.

01:08:26.200 --> 01:08:28.080
Please look at the slide.

01:08:28.240 --> 01:08:30.580
At high interest rates, firms

01:08:30.590 --> 01:08:33.200
will borrow little money in

01:08:33.210 --> 01:08:35.500
banks and, accordingly,

01:08:35.840 --> 01:08:37.920
invest, buy new equipment

01:08:37.930 --> 01:08:39.680
will also be for small

01:08:39.690 --> 01:08:41.920
amounts.

01:08:41.930 --> 01:08:45.320
At low interest rates, firms

01:08:46.520 --> 01:08:49.200
borrow more and their investment

01:08:49.210 --> 01:08:52.140
costs increase due to the growth

01:08:52.150 --> 01:08:54.420
of borrowing funds.

01:08:55.020 --> 01:08:57.240
Return to the previous slide.

01:08:57.280 --> 01:08:59.340
Even one slide back,

01:08:59.350 --> 01:09:00.820
let's go.

