What else depends on the investment demand

01:09:03.810 --> 01:09:05.400
of companies?

01:09:05.620 --> 01:09:08.680
of national income.

01:09:08.860 --> 01:09:09.720
How to understand?

01:09:09.730 --> 01:09:10.840
Why so?

01:09:11.720 --> 01:09:13.600
Imagine that the national income

01:09:13.610 --> 01:09:14.540
has increased.

01:09:14.940 --> 01:09:16.880
All consumers' incomes have increased.

01:09:17.480 --> 01:09:19.300
They started spending more.

01:09:20.180 --> 01:09:24.380
So the demand for the products of the companies has increased.

01:09:25.160 --> 01:09:27.000
First, companies are trying

01:09:27.010 --> 01:09:31.320
to meet this demand by means of

01:09:31.330 --> 01:09:33.160
active production in capacities.

01:09:33.880 --> 01:09:36.700
But sooner or later, with the expansion

01:09:36.710 --> 01:09:39.360
of demand, they will have to increase

01:09:39.370 --> 01:09:41.340
their production capacity.

01:09:41.560 --> 01:09:42.580
That is, to buy new equipment,

01:09:42.590 --> 01:09:45.460
to buy new buildings,

01:09:45.470 --> 01:09:47.540
structures.

01:09:47.800 --> 01:09:48.960
That is, to make

01:09:48.970 --> 01:09:50.760
investment costs.

01:09:52.880 --> 01:09:54.420
The higher the national income, the

01:09:54.430 --> 01:09:56.900
higher the investment costs of the

01:09:56.910 --> 01:09:57.660
companies.

01:10:00.620 --> 01:10:03.480
Expected return on investment.

01:10:04.500 --> 01:10:06.760
The third factor.

01:10:07.180 --> 01:10:09.300
He is also very important.

01:10:09.580 --> 01:10:11.840
Why do companies make

01:10:11.850 --> 01:10:13.760
investment expenses?

01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:16.180
in terms of future profits.

01:10:16.820 --> 01:10:19.660
And there are expectations of future

01:10:19.670 --> 01:10:23.520
profits for firms favorable, they

01:10:23.530 --> 01:10:26.280
will invest more with other equal.

01:10:27.760 --> 01:10:30.180
Consequently, investment costs

01:10:30.190 --> 01:10:31.760
are increasing.

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:33.880
The overall demand is growing.

