01:34:55.920 --> 01:34:57.220
And what led to what?

01:34:57.600 --> 01:34:58.940
The car has temporarily solved

01:34:58.950 --> 01:35:00.460
its sales problems.

01:35:01.920 --> 01:35:06.420
In other words, by reducing our imports, we

01:35:06.430 --> 01:35:08.600
increased our purchases of what?

01:35:10.060 --> 01:35:11.940
Import of replacement products.

01:35:12.500 --> 01:35:15.660
The demand for domestic

01:35:15.670 --> 01:35:17.760
goods has increased.

01:35:18.680 --> 01:35:20.560
But all - let's make it clear again, let's

01:35:20.570 --> 01:35:21.800
get the outcome.

01:35:26.120 --> 01:35:31.140
The lower the real exchange rate,

01:35:31.420 --> 01:35:34.680
the cheaper our goods are in general

01:35:34.690 --> 01:35:36.740
relative to foreign.

01:35:37.400 --> 01:35:40.300
The more our exports and the

01:35:40.310 --> 01:35:42.700
less our imports.

01:35:43.000 --> 01:35:46.160
This means that our net exports are greater.

01:35:46.380 --> 01:35:48.940
This is the result of the increased

01:35:48.950 --> 01:35:51.560
demand for Russian goods.

01:35:53.280 --> 01:35:54.520
Yes, here is something else.

01:35:54.860 --> 01:35:56.680
What are we watching now?

01:35:58.860 --> 01:36:01.440
The trend has changed drastically here.

01:36:05.040 --> 01:36:06.280
Not only do we have prices

01:36:06.290 --> 01:36:08.260
continue to rise, although at a

01:36:08.270 --> 01:36:09.720
more copper pace than before.

01:36:10.180 --> 01:36:11.500
But what else is happening?

01:36:13.280 --> 01:36:17.160
The nominal rate of the ruble,

01:36:17.170 --> 01:36:18.560
at least against the dollar,

01:36:18.570 --> 01:36:21.400
is now also rising.

01:36:24.260 --> 01:36:28.000
The real course has grown.

01:36:30.720 --> 01:36:35.300
This generally has a negative

01:36:35.310 --> 01:36:37.720
impact on our exports and is

01:36:37.730 --> 01:36:39.720
very beneficial for our imports.

01:36:40.760 --> 01:36:43.800
We are again travelling in foreign brands,

01:36:43.810 --> 01:36:48.780
resting in Turkey, buying imported

01:36:48.790 --> 01:36:50.260
clothes again, for example.

01:36:50.520 --> 01:36:52.820
Well, I hope you understand why

01:36:53.140 --> 01:36:56.540
Americans are making claims

01:36:56.550 --> 01:37:00.920
to China about the Chinese

01:37:03.510 --> 01:37:07.510
being lowering the yuan.

01:37:07.810 --> 01:37:10.250
Why are the Chinese down the course?

01:37:13.040 --> 01:37:14.880
This is the usual strategy

01:37:14.890 --> 01:37:17.000
of a developing economy

01:37:17.010 --> 01:37:18.860
–ining a low rate of national

01:37:18.870 --> 01:37:20.100
currency.

01:37:20.110 --> 01:37:20.460
Why is?

01:37:21.420 --> 01:37:22.880
Because the low rate of the

01:37:22.890 --> 01:37:25.580
national currency promotes the export of

01:37:25.590 --> 01:37:28.120
the country and, on the contrary,

01:37:28.320 --> 01:37:31.680
makes it difficult to import foreign

01:37:31.690 --> 01:37:33.100
goods to this country.

01:37:33.260 --> 01:37:36.760
That is, the low rate is a

01:37:36.770 --> 01:37:39.840
factor in ensuring competitive advantages

01:37:39.850 --> 01:37:41.100
of the national developing

01:37:41.110 --> 01:37:43.460
economy.

01:37:43.470 --> 01:37:47.060
So, we have finished considering

01:37:47.070 --> 01:37:51.200
the combined demand curve.

01:37:51.420 --> 01:37:53.640
But, if you think about it, the

01:37:53.650 --> 01:37:55.840
combined demand curve itself does

01:37:55.850 --> 01:38:00.380
not yet show what the price level

01:38:00.390 --> 01:38:03.840
and real GDP will be in the economy.

01:38:04.440 --> 01:38:06.760
It only says that the lower the

01:38:06.770 --> 01:38:10.120
price level, the greater the

01:38:10.130 --> 01:38:12.260
total demand for real GDP.

01:38:12.360 --> 01:38:15.980
But what will be the price of GDP,

01:38:15.990 --> 01:38:18.200
only one cannot say anything.

01:38:19.380 --> 01:38:22.160
The overall proposal function

01:38:22.170 --> 01:38:23.900
will be considered.

01:38:24.780 --> 01:38:25.780
Please look at the

01:38:25.790 --> 01:38:27.080
next slide.

01:38:28.840 --> 01:38:31.360
Total supply is the real

01:38:31.370 --> 01:38:34.320
GDP that all producers

01:38:34.330 --> 01:38:37.920
are willing to produce and sell

01:38:37.930 --> 01:38:41.580
during a given time at different

01:38:41.590 --> 01:38:43.780
price levels.

01:38:46.020 --> 01:38:48.020
Total demand is how much all

01:38:48.030 --> 01:38:51.040
consumers are willing to buy,

01:38:51.050 --> 01:38:52.920
and total supply is how much

01:38:52.930 --> 01:38:56.300
all producers are willing to sell.

01:38:59.320 --> 01:39:02.500
To analyze the function of aggregate

01:39:02.510 --> 01:39:07.100
supply, we will have to distinguish

01:39:07.160 --> 01:39:10.000
short-term and long-term periods

01:39:10.010 --> 01:39:12.060
in macroeconomics.

01:39:15.550 --> 01:39:17.090
A long-term period in

01:39:17.100 --> 01:39:20.530
macroeconomics is a period

01:39:20.540 --> 01:39:24.050
during which prices of both commodities

01:39:24.150 --> 01:39:27.090
and resources can freely

01:39:27.100 --> 01:39:30.970
fluctuate up or down.

01:39:32.130 --> 01:39:34.870
Accordingly, the long-term curve

01:39:34.880 --> 01:39:36.770
of the aggregate supply, please

01:39:36.780 --> 01:39:40.930
look at the slide, vertically

01:39:41.310 --> 01:39:42.790
at the level of the

01:39:42.800 --> 01:39:44.650
potential GDP.

01:39:51.560 --> 01:39:53.940
In other words, the behavior

01:39:53.950 --> 01:39:56.780
of the economy in the long term

01:39:56.790 --> 01:40:00.360
is determined by the classical model.

01:40:03.150 --> 01:40:05.190
According to the point of view of economists

01:40:05.230 --> 01:40:07.970
called the classics, the free market,

01:40:07.980 --> 01:40:11.130
if not interfered, will sooner

01:40:11.140 --> 01:40:15.370
or later result in the real

01:40:15.380 --> 01:40:19.070
GDP becoming equal to the

01:40:19.080 --> 01:40:20.750
potential level.

01:40:22.100 --> 01:40:24.320
What is potential GDP?

01:40:26.230 --> 01:40:29.670
The potential GDP is the GDP that is

01:40:29.680 --> 01:40:33.130
attainable at the fullest possible extent

01:40:33.140 --> 01:40:36.330
with the full use of all available resources.

01:40:38.180 --> 01:40:39.840
I want to emphasize again.

01:40:40.060 --> 01:40:43.020
The classics emphasized, and

01:40:43.030 --> 01:40:45.060
this corresponds to the

01:40:45.070 --> 01:40:50.590
observed real, that a market economy

01:40:50.600 --> 01:40:53.010
ultimately leads to, in the

01:40:53.020 --> 01:40:56.870
long run, that all available

01:40:56.880 --> 01:41:00.330
resources are used at full

01:41:00.340 --> 01:41:02.130
capacity.

01:41:02.530 --> 01:41:05.850
The balance GDP is equal to

01:41:05.860 --> 01:41:09.050
the potential level.

01:41:12.760 --> 01:41:15.180
The potential GDP depends on the

01:41:15.190 --> 01:41:17.520
amount of resources available in

01:41:17.530 --> 01:41:20.660
the economy and on technical progress.

01:41:22.490 --> 01:41:25.170
But the potential GDP or economic

01:41:25.180 --> 01:41:28.590
opportunities are not dependent

01:41:28.600 --> 01:41:29.810
on the level of prices.

01:41:30.830 --> 01:41:33.150
Prices can be higher and lower.

01:41:34.290 --> 01:41:37.870
And again, the economy sooner

01:41:37.880 --> 01:41:40.850
or later comes to

01:41:40.860 --> 01:41:44.190
potential GDP at higher or lower

01:41:44.200 --> 01:41:45.890
prices.

01:41:46.130 --> 01:41:49.390
This means that the long-

01:41:49.400 --> 01:41:51.730
term summary proposition

01:41:51.740 --> 01:41:54.570
curve is a vertical line,

01:41:54.580 --> 01:41:58.690
as shown in the picture

01:41:58.700 --> 01:42:00.410
you see on the slide.

01:42:02.830 --> 01:42:04.730
The long-term function of the aggregate

01:42:04.740 --> 01:42:06.430
offer can shift to the right

01:42:06.440 --> 01:42:07.930
or to the left.

01:42:10.280 --> 01:42:13.040
Imagine that the amount of resources

01:42:13.050 --> 01:42:15.840
available in this economy

01:42:15.850 --> 01:42:18.400
has increased over time.

01:42:19.400 --> 01:42:22.740
Well, for example, the population increased,

01:42:25.640 --> 01:42:27.890
capital accumulated.

01:42:29.170 --> 01:42:30.430
Under capital, I want to emphasize

01:42:30.440 --> 01:42:32.410
again, we understand in macroeconomics

01:42:32.420 --> 01:42:34.570
the means of production.

01:42:35.330 --> 01:42:38.190
In the economy more machines, machines, equipment.

01:42:38.830 --> 01:42:41.010
Finally, there is technical progress.

01:42:41.150 --> 01:42:45.490
This means that the potential GDP

01:42:45.500 --> 01:42:47.610
is increasing.

01:42:50.280 --> 01:42:53.620
And if that is the case, the long-

01:42:53.630 --> 01:42:55.480
term summary supply curve begins

01:42:55.490 --> 01:42:58.280
to shift to the right.

01:42:58.360 --> 01:43:00.300
If, on the contrary, there is a regression

01:43:00.310 --> 01:43:02.820
in the economy, the amount of resources

01:43:02.830 --> 01:43:04.820
is reduced.

01:43:05.180 --> 01:43:07.600
Instead of technological progress,

01:43:07.610 --> 01:43:10.140
the regression is technical.

01:43:10.620 --> 01:43:12.820
In this, quite rare case, the long-

01:43:14.240 --> 01:43:16.400
term function of the aggregate

01:43:16.410 --> 01:43:19.500
offer shifts to the left.

01:43:19.510 --> 01:43:22.720
Now let's talk about the

01:43:22.730 --> 01:43:25.800
short-term function of the aggregate offer.

01:43:28.730 --> 01:43:33.510
In the short term, prices for goods and

01:43:33.520 --> 01:43:38.250
resources are less flexible than in the long term.

01:43:39.230 --> 01:43:41.470
Moreover, sometimes they

01:43:41.480 --> 01:43:44.010
are unchanged.

01:43:51.630 --> 01:43:53.630
Accordingly, the short-term

01:43:53.640 --> 01:43:55.570
curve of the aggregate supply

01:43:55.580 --> 01:43:58.110
can be horizontal or have

01:43:58.120 --> 01:44:00.290
a rising slope.

01:44:00.710 --> 01:44:02.270
A positive trend.

01:44:02.280 --> 01:44:04.310
Please look at the slide.

01:44:06.420 --> 01:44:09.720
What does the left schedule say?

01:44:11.080 --> 01:44:13.700
That the level of prices in the economy is

01:44:15.260 --> 01:44:18.540
set, and producers have the opportunity

01:44:18.550 --> 01:44:23.020
to increase the volume of real GDP at a

01:44:23.030 --> 01:44:24.180
given level of prices.

01:44:24.190 --> 01:44:27.540
There would be demand for their products.

01:44:28.700 --> 01:44:30.960
Usually, such a function,

01:44:31.140 --> 01:44:33.540
the horizontal function of the aggregate

01:44:35.020 --> 01:44:37.770
supply, occurs when the actual

01:44:37.780 --> 01:44:40.930
GDP is significantly less

01:44:40.940 --> 01:44:43.290
than the potential.

01:44:43.930 --> 01:44:46.070
The economy is working with

01:44:46.080 --> 01:44:47.730
a great underload.

01:44:48.090 --> 01:44:50.750
There are a lot of unused

01:44:50.760 --> 01:44:53.270
resources.

01:44:53.370 --> 01:44:56.190
Figuratively speaking, mass unemployment

01:44:56.200 --> 01:44:58.770
in the economy, factories are

01:44:58.780 --> 01:45:01.570
stagnant, fields are not sowed.

01:45:01.930 --> 01:45:03.230
Why does this happen?

01:45:03.970 --> 01:45:07.350
Probably because of the low

01:45:07.360 --> 01:45:10.090
overall demand for

01:45:10.100 --> 01:45:11.350
domestic products.

01:45:13.590 --> 01:45:15.270
If the overall demand increased,

01:45:15.280 --> 01:45:17.610
it would be not difficult for manufacturers

01:45:17.620 --> 01:45:20.590
to engage today's unemployed in

01:45:22.150 --> 01:45:24.440
production, increase the use of

01:45:24.450 --> 01:45:26.820
equipment, that is, without

01:45:26.830 --> 01:45:28.960
raising prices.

01:45:30.630 --> 01:45:33.350
That is, at the same price level,

01:45:33.360 --> 01:45:35.530
producers could freely increase the

01:45:35.540 --> 01:45:37.510
volume of production.

01:45:38.110 --> 01:45:40.090
And the short-term curve of the

01:45:40.100 --> 01:45:43.790
aggregate offer is, it turns out, horizontal.

01:45:45.920 --> 01:45:48.140
Another case is more frequent.

01:45:48.160 --> 01:45:51.320
Look at the right chart when

01:45:51.330 --> 01:45:53.580
the short-term aggregate

01:45:53.590 --> 01:45:56.640
bid curve has a positive tilt.

01:45:58.260 --> 01:45:59.460
What does this mean?

01:45:59.540 --> 01:46:03.360
That in a short period, producers

01:46:03.370 --> 01:46:09.260
respond to the rise in prices by the

01:46:10.180 --> 01:46:13.340
growth of real GDP, the growth

01:46:13.350 --> 01:46:15.220
of real production.

01:46:15.920 --> 01:46:18.920
That means higher prices

01:46:18.930 --> 01:46:21.560
are encouraging producers

01:46:22.520 --> 01:46:26.360
to produce and sell more products.

01:46:27.040 --> 01:46:29.340
The real GDP, i.e.

01:46:29.350 --> 01:46:32.300
the total supply from

01:46:32.310 --> 01:46:34.800
all producers, is growing.

01:46:40.170 --> 01:46:42.050
Remember, I said that the

01:46:42.060 --> 01:46:43.710
long-term aggregate proposition function

01:46:43.720 --> 01:46:46.050
can shift to the right, sometimes

01:46:46.060 --> 01:46:48.490
to the left.

01:46:50.170 --> 01:46:52.190
The short-term function of the aggregate

01:46:52.200 --> 01:46:54.750
offer may shift downward, but more

01:46:55.270 --> 01:46:56.770
often all upwards.

01:47:00.160 --> 01:47:02.020
Why can this happen?

01:47:06.660 --> 01:47:09.760
In fact, the short-term function

01:47:09.770 --> 01:47:12.080
of the aggregate supply is related

01:47:12.090 --> 01:47:15.680
to the cost of the producers per

01:47:15.690 --> 01:47:17.840
unit of product.

01:47:18.940 --> 01:47:21.540
Imagine that the resources have been

01:47:26.870 --> 01:47:29.000
spent by all the companies.

01:47:30.020 --> 01:47:31.320
What will this lead to?

01:47:33.980 --> 01:47:37.060
That all companies will be forced

01:47:38.690 --> 01:47:41.680
to raise their sales prices when producing

01:47:41.690 --> 01:47:44.760
the previous volume of products.

01:47:45.020 --> 01:47:46.740
Accordingly, the short-term curve

01:47:46.750 --> 01:47:48.520
of the aggregate proposition, though

01:47:48.800 --> 01:47:50.240
horizontal, though rising,

01:47:50.250 --> 01:47:52.400
shifts to the right.

01:47:54.820 --> 01:47:56.120
The simplest example.

01:47:56.600 --> 01:47:59.380
Imagine that the RAU of the EU

01:47:59.390 --> 01:48:01.960
has increased electricity tariffs.

01:48:05.070 --> 01:48:06.410
What will this lead to?

01:48:08.050 --> 01:48:11.050
All companies will have increased

01:48:11.060 --> 01:48:14.950
costs on equal terms.

01:48:17.300 --> 01:48:20.520
This means that they will have to increase

01:48:20.530 --> 01:48:24.420
their prices at previous volume

01:48:24.430 --> 01:48:25.860
of production.

01:48:26.400 --> 01:48:27.780
And the short-term curve

01:48:27.790 --> 01:48:30.400
of the total supply will go,

01:48:30.410 --> 01:48:31.620
I repeat, up.

01:48:34.370 --> 01:48:38.110
Now to the third question of the topic.

01:48:41.460 --> 01:48:43.940
macroeconomic balance of the economy.

01:48:48.780 --> 01:48:49.460
What is it?

01:48:52.030 --> 01:48:54.770
Macroeconomic balance is

01:48:54.780 --> 01:48:57.450
achieved when the total

01:48:57.460 --> 01:49:02.150
demand is equal to the total supply.

01:49:06.030 --> 01:49:07.480
Please look at the slide.

01:49:15.010 --> 01:49:18.170
I have said that in the long run,

01:49:18.180 --> 01:49:21.610
the total supply is aimed at

01:49:21.620 --> 01:49:24.870
the level of the potential GDP.

01:49:28.730 --> 01:49:31.510
Accordingly, macroeconomic balance

01:49:31.520 --> 01:49:34.270
is achieved at the point of intersection

01:49:34.280 --> 01:49:36.730
of the combined demand curve

01:49:36.740 --> 01:49:40.070
and the long-term combined

01:49:40.080 --> 01:49:41.210
supply curve.

01:49:42.350 --> 01:49:48.190
What happens if the overall demand increases?

01:49:48.730 --> 01:49:51.290
For example, the central bank will increase

01:49:51.300 --> 01:49:52.830
the money mass in the economy.

01:49:54.940 --> 01:49:57.220
Total demand will grow, but

01:49:57.230 --> 01:49:59.840
in the long run it will only affect

01:49:59.850 --> 01:50:01.740
prices.

01:50:02.200 --> 01:50:04.660
The output will remain the same

01:50:04.670 --> 01:50:07.460
and equal to the potential GDP.

01:50:11.320 --> 01:50:14.980
Well, the short-term curve of the

01:50:14.990 --> 01:50:16.940
aggregate offer, it does not play

01:50:16.950 --> 01:50:18.600
an independent role here.

01:50:18.610 --> 01:50:21.900
It simply goes through the point

01:50:21.910 --> 01:50:24.740
of long-term macroeconomic equilibrium.

01:50:26.640 --> 01:50:29.420
It is as if it is adjusted to the intersection

01:50:29.430 --> 01:50:31.820
of these two functions.

01:50:32.040 --> 01:50:34.080
The function of aggregate

01:50:34.090 --> 01:50:37.020
demand and long-term supply curve.

01:50:40.790 --> 01:50:42.730
In the short term, the situation is more complicated.

01:50:46.220 --> 01:50:49.160
Please look at the slide.

01:50:49.480 --> 01:50:52.180
Macroeconomic balance is at the

01:50:52.190 --> 01:50:55.720
point of intersection of the curve

01:50:55.730 --> 01:50:59.670
of aggregate demand and the

01:50:59.680 --> 01:51:03.010
short-term curve of aggregate supply.

01:51:04.400 --> 01:51:07.760
At the same time, the balanced

01:51:07.770 --> 01:51:09.260
GDP may not coincide

01:51:09.270 --> 01:51:11.260
with the potential, as

01:51:11.270 --> 01:51:13.460
we see in the slide chart.

01:51:14.950 --> 01:51:16.910
Please look at.

01:51:17.790 --> 01:51:20.610
Balance GDP is defined by

01:51:20.620 --> 01:51:23.350
the intersection of the

01:51:23.360 --> 01:51:26.150
short-term supply and the combined

01:51:26.160 --> 01:51:28.630
demand function.

01:51:28.640 --> 01:51:32.150
At the same time, the balanced GDP is

01:51:32.160 --> 01:51:35.130
less than the potential, that is, the

01:51:35.140 --> 01:51:37.370
economy is underloaded.

01:51:37.930 --> 01:51:39.270
Why underload?

01:51:40.980 --> 01:51:41.980
Small total demand.

01:51:43.200 --> 01:51:46.120
If it were more, imagine,

01:51:46.130 --> 01:51:48.140
well, that the state could

01:51:48.150 --> 01:51:51.560
stimulate the overall demand

01:51:51.570 --> 01:51:53.260
with its methods.

01:51:54.380 --> 01:51:56.400
Whatever his mind, imagine.

01:51:57.360 --> 01:52:00.160
Total demand would increase and the

01:52:00.170 --> 01:52:01.760
combined demand curve would

01:52:01.770 --> 01:52:03.480
shift to the right.

01:52:03.640 --> 01:52:05.220
And it is possible that in this

01:52:05.230 --> 01:52:09.060
case the balanced GDP would be the same

01:52:09.070 --> 01:52:10.700
as the potential.

01:52:12.240 --> 01:52:14.580
Here let's take this moment

01:52:14.590 --> 01:52:17.840
and look at it more carefully.

01:52:18.080 --> 01:52:20.220
Next slide, please see

01:52:20.230 --> 01:52:23.220
the change in the balance

01:52:23.230 --> 01:52:24.820
of the economy.

01:52:27.380 --> 01:52:28.460
Let us understand.

01:52:28.820 --> 01:52:29.920
It only at first glance looks

01:52:29.930 --> 01:52:31.800
like such a confusing picture.

01:52:32.060 --> 01:52:33.500
There is really nothing complicated

01:52:33.510 --> 01:52:34.200
in it.

01:52:34.860 --> 01:52:38.420
See also vertical function.

01:52:40.200 --> 01:52:43.120
Long-term function of the aggregate offer.

01:52:43.460 --> 01:52:46.640
It goes vertically from point U1.

01:52:47.260 --> 01:52:49.480
So what is U1?

01:52:50.780 --> 01:52:52.580
The potential GDP.

01:52:55.200 --> 01:53:00.580
Short-term function of the aggregate offer.

01:53:03.400 --> 01:53:06.020
SRAs0

01:53:08.380 --> 01:53:12.480
The total demand function AD0.

01:53:12.820 --> 01:53:15.660
The macroeconomic balance is

01:53:15.670 --> 01:53:18.360
achieved at the point G0.

01:53:20.280 --> 01:53:22.000
Again, what are we watching?

01:53:22.380 --> 01:53:23.700
The overall demand is small.

01:53:24.820 --> 01:53:28.280
GDP is less than the

01:53:28.290 --> 01:53:29.860
potential level.

01:53:31.450 --> 01:53:35.570
Suppose the overall demand has

01:53:35.580 --> 01:53:37.370
increased for some reason.

01:53:38.330 --> 01:53:39.490
The state has tried to stimulate

01:53:39.530 --> 01:53:40.790
the overall demand.

01:53:41.150 --> 01:53:42.490
Maybe something else happened.

01:53:43.330 --> 01:53:44.890
But overall demand has increased.

01:53:47.010 --> 01:53:49.370
Accordingly, the AD curve, the aggregate

01:53:49.380 --> 01:53:51.970
demand curve is shifting to where?

01:53:53.050 --> 01:53:53.770
to the right.

01:53:55.170 --> 01:53:56.670
Where is the cross now?

01:53:58.030 --> 01:54:00.150
At the E1.

01:54:00.690 --> 01:54:03.290
We have increased prices, the level of prices has risen.

01:54:03.300 --> 01:54:08.470
But the balanced GDP is now equal to the potential.

01:54:08.830 --> 01:54:10.170
The policy of stimulating

01:54:10.180 --> 01:54:12.430
overall demand has yielded its fruits.

01:54:13.150 --> 01:54:15.290
Total demand has increased, and the balanced

01:54:15.300 --> 01:54:16.470
GDP has also increased.

01:54:20.630 --> 01:54:23.170
What if the overall demand

01:54:23.180 --> 01:54:24.770
increases?

01:54:25.790 --> 01:54:28.870
The AD curve will then move further to the

01:54:28.880 --> 01:54:31.610
right, already in the position of AD2.

01:54:33.180 --> 01:54:36.260
In the short term, the point

01:54:36.270 --> 01:54:39.980
of balance will be E2.

01:54:40.500 --> 01:54:42.220
Well, the point of intersection

01:54:42.230 --> 01:54:44.640
between the short-term curve of aggregate

01:54:44.650 --> 01:54:46.520
supply and the new curve of

01:54:46.530 --> 01:54:48.380
aggregate demand.

01:54:49.080 --> 01:54:50.720
But what are we watching now?

01:54:52.940 --> 01:54:55.760
We are seeing a warming economy.

01:54:56.600 --> 01:54:59.680
The economy is overloaded.

01:55:00.640 --> 01:55:04.780
GDP is higher than

01:55:04.790 --> 01:55:06.680
potential.

01:55:06.690 --> 01:55:08.560
In a short period of time, this is possible.

01:55:09.320 --> 01:55:12.780
This means not the normal, but

01:55:12.790 --> 01:55:14.760
the superintensive use of all

01:55:14.770 --> 01:55:16.180
resources.

01:55:16.420 --> 01:55:19.020
For example, a normal working day,

01:55:19.480 --> 01:55:24.540
8 hours with a 5-day working week.

01:55:25.640 --> 01:55:27.620
But in a short period, people can

01:55:27.630 --> 01:55:29.420
work 10 hours, 10 hours without

01:55:29.430 --> 01:55:30.160
weekends.

01:55:31.100 --> 01:55:33.240
We say that the labor resources

01:55:33.250 --> 01:55:35.700
are being used superintensively.

01:55:37.440 --> 01:55:39.540
Some equipment is stopped

01:55:39.550 --> 01:55:42.060
for prevention periodically.

01:55:42.960 --> 01:55:45.120
But you can allow a situation in

01:55:45.130 --> 01:55:46.760
which the equipment for

01:55:46.770 --> 01:55:50.160
prevention is not stopped in a short period of time.

01:55:50.460 --> 01:55:51.120
and so on.

01:55:51.980 --> 01:55:55.420
This is why we have learned that the economy

01:55:55.430 --> 01:55:57.460
is overloaded with resources.

01:55:57.470 --> 01:56:00.860
I repeat, it is used superintensively.

01:56:01.060 --> 01:56:03.260
GDP is more than potential.

01:56:04.900 --> 01:56:07.700
But when the resource is used

01:56:07.710 --> 01:56:11.040
superintensively, they become deficitary.

01:56:11.640 --> 01:56:14.780
The prices for them are beginning to rise.

01:56:18.870 --> 01:56:22.230
This leads to the fact that the costs of the

01:56:22.240 --> 01:56:24.450
companies are beginning to increase.

01:56:24.910 --> 01:56:27.330
And when the costs of the companies

01:56:27.340 --> 01:56:29.650
per unit of product begin to increase,

01:56:30.350 --> 01:56:32.430
the short-term function of the aggregate

01:56:32.440 --> 01:56:35.530
supply goes up.

01:56:35.540 --> 01:56:40.030
This is where it moved to S R

01:56:40.040 --> 01:56:41.710
A S 1.

01:56:44.020 --> 01:56:46.060
Where do we end up in the end?

01:56:48.100 --> 01:56:49.740
Eventually, the balance returns

01:56:49.750 --> 01:56:53.260
to the E3 point.

01:56:53.820 --> 01:56:55.360
That is, the economy eventually

01:56:55.370 --> 01:56:56.960
returns to potential

01:56:56.970 --> 01:57:00.480
GDP, but at the highest

01:57:00.490 --> 01:57:02.500
possible price level.

01:57:03.040 --> 01:57:05.600
P3 in my example.

01:57:07.230 --> 01:57:11.610
Let us go to the fourth question.

01:57:16.650 --> 01:57:21.650
The fourth question is called the multiplier effect.

01:57:23.470 --> 01:57:27.150
Look at the interesting

01:57:27.160 --> 01:57:31.110
macroeconomic patterns.

01:57:34.900 --> 01:57:38.180
Suppose, with a given level of

01:57:40.820 --> 01:57:43.530
national income, one of the

01:57:43.540 --> 01:57:46.170
economic agents increases its

01:57:46.180 --> 01:57:48.950
expenses.

01:57:50.250 --> 01:57:52.770
Well, let's say household incomes

01:57:52.780 --> 01:57:56.110
have not changed, but they have

01:57:56.120 --> 01:57:57.790
decided to spend more for

01:57:57.800 --> 01:57:58.890
some reason.

01:58:00.250 --> 01:58:03.590
Or the revenues of the firms remained

01:58:04.210 --> 01:58:05.930
the same, but they believe

01:58:05.940 --> 01:58:08.270
the business prospects are favorable

01:58:08.280 --> 01:58:10.790
and decided to increase investment

01:58:10.800 --> 01:58:14.250
costs with their current revenues,

01:58:14.410 --> 01:58:16.490
to purchase new equipment.

01:58:17.010 --> 01:58:19.930
The state has decided to increase

01:58:19.940 --> 01:58:21.210
its expenses.

01:58:21.310 --> 01:58:24.790
Or foreigners, with other equals, decided

01:58:24.800 --> 01:58:28.730
to increase the purchase of our goods.

01:58:32.210 --> 01:58:35.170
This means that so-called autonomous

01:58:35.180 --> 01:58:38.150
costs have increased.

01:58:38.470 --> 01:58:43.070
Autonomous expenses are expenses

01:58:43.390 --> 01:58:45.390
that are made with a constant

01:58:45.400 --> 01:58:47.430
income.

01:58:47.670 --> 01:58:51.390
If your income has not changed, but you

01:58:51.400 --> 01:58:54.290
have increased your expenses, it

01:58:54.300 --> 01:58:57.470
means that your own expenses have increased.

01:58:57.910 --> 01:58:59.730
If the company's income did not change, they

01:58:59.740 --> 01:59:02.270
increased their expenses.

01:59:02.550 --> 01:59:04.230
This means that the companies have carried

01:59:04.240 --> 01:59:05.830
out autonomous expenses.

01:59:07.240 --> 01:59:09.140
Expenditure on previous income.

01:59:14.230 --> 01:59:18.810
Imagine this situation.

01:59:19.770 --> 01:59:23.110
The companies increased

01:59:23.120 --> 01:59:26.310
their investment costs by some amount.

01:59:30.300 --> 01:59:31.890
Conditionally for 100 rubles.

01:59:34.330 --> 01:59:35.390
But that is interesting.

01:59:42.410 --> 01:59:45.450
Very soon we will see that

01:59:45.460 --> 01:59:49.010
the combined demand and national

01:59:49.020 --> 01:59:54.350
income, and real GDP, will increase

01:59:54.360 --> 01:59:57.410
by a greater amount compared to

01:59:57.420 --> 01:59:59.490
the initial change in autonomous

02:00:00.010 --> 02:00:01.390
spending.

02:00:04.490 --> 02:00:06.110
Conditionally, you have increased your expenses

02:00:06.120 --> 02:00:09.210
by 100 rubles, and then the economy

02:00:09.220 --> 02:00:11.830
will go through a chain reaction, which

02:00:12.270 --> 02:00:15.650
will lead to the fact that the overall

02:00:15.660 --> 02:00:17.550
demand of all consumers will increase

02:00:17.560 --> 02:00:19.650
not by 100 rubles, but by a larger amount.

02:00:21.110 --> 02:00:25.430
This is what the multiplier effect is.

02:00:26.490 --> 02:00:29.630
Please read the definition on the

02:00:29.640 --> 02:00:30.750
slide.

02:00:31.090 --> 02:00:33.750
The multiplier of autonomous expenses

02:00:33.760 --> 02:00:38.350
is a factor that shows how much

02:00:38.360 --> 02:00:40.170
rubles the combined demand

02:00:40.180 --> 02:00:42.750
and national income change

02:00:42.760 --> 02:00:46.170
when autonomous expenses change

02:00:46.180 --> 02:00:49.050
by one ruble.

02:00:49.610 --> 02:00:52.350
Well, that is, if, say, the firms increased

02:00:52.360 --> 02:00:53.790
their expenses by 100 rubles, and

02:00:56.600 --> 02:00:58.910
the demand is ultimately aggregate,

02:00:58.920 --> 02:01:03.610
this means that each ruble of autonomous

02:01:03.620 --> 02:01:07.970
expenses led to an increase in the

02:01:07.980 --> 02:01:10.550
aggregate demand and GDP by 5

02:01:10.560 --> 02:01:12.570
rubles.

02:01:12.770 --> 02:01:16.010
The multiplier is equal to 5.

02:01:17.750 --> 02:01:22.110
So, I'll try to illustrate the effect

02:01:22.120 --> 02:01:24.510
of the multiplier of autonomous costs

02:01:24.520 --> 02:01:28.410
on a simple numerical example.

02:01:30.210 --> 02:01:31.290
Well here, look at it.

02:01:32.470 --> 02:01:36.530
Companies have increased their autonomous

02:01:36.540 --> 02:01:38.930
expenses.

02:01:39.030 --> 02:01:41.970
That is, the expenses of this income.

02:01:41.990 --> 02:01:44.170
The national income did not change, but

02:01:44.570 --> 02:01:46.590
the companies increased their expenses

02:01:46.600 --> 02:01:48.730
with this income.

02:01:48.740 --> 02:01:50.470
For 100 rubles.

02:01:51.330 --> 02:01:54.550
What does it mean that companies have increased their expenses?

02:01:54.930 --> 02:01:57.910
This means that they, for example,

02:01:58.590 --> 02:02:01.870
ordered new equipment

02:02:01.880 --> 02:02:04.630
for 100 rubles.

02:02:05.470 --> 02:02:09.390
The money is spent, the equipment is delivered.

02:02:14.310 --> 02:02:19.090
So, the combined demand and national

02:02:19.100 --> 02:02:23.170
income increased at the beginning

02:02:23.180 --> 02:02:24.590
by 100 rubles.

02:02:26.930 --> 02:02:28.930
Here it is assumed that the

02:02:28.940 --> 02:02:31.230
short-term function of the aggregate

02:02:31.240 --> 02:02:33.110
offer is horizontal.

02:02:33.120 --> 02:02:37.650
The growth of production is equal to the

02:02:37.660 --> 02:02:39.390
growth of the total...

02:02:39.400 --> 02:02:42.690
Increase in total demand.

02:02:46.150 --> 02:02:48.450
The total demand increased by 100 rubles.

02:02:49.810 --> 02:02:52.430
In response to the increase in demand for

02:02:52.440 --> 02:02:57.210
100 rubles, the workers of the machinery manufacturers

02:02:57.220 --> 02:03:01.830
produced and sold machines for this amount.

02:03:05.920 --> 02:03:09.840
So, these 100 rubles

02:03:09.850 --> 02:03:12.320
the engineers received

02:03:12.330 --> 02:03:14.700
as their income.

02:03:16.680 --> 02:03:19.800
For customers, the cost is 100 rubles.

02:03:20.140 --> 02:03:23.020
But this cost turned into the income

02:03:23.030 --> 02:03:25.900
of those who produced the equipment.

02:03:27.200 --> 02:03:30.320
What did the workers do?

02:03:32.400 --> 02:03:35.200
Well, suppose, having received

02:03:35.210 --> 02:03:38.580
an additional income of 100 rubles,

02:03:39.200 --> 02:03:43.460
the engineers spent part of that

02:03:45.820 --> 02:03:49.380
income, and saved the other part.

02:03:50.240 --> 02:03:52.880
In this simple model, we do not consider taxes.

02:03:54.240 --> 02:03:56.200
All additional income

02:03:56.210 --> 02:03:58.480
is divided into additional

02:03:58.490 --> 02:04:01.640
consumption and additional savings.

02:04:05.200 --> 02:04:09.280
The increase in consumer spending

02:04:10.740 --> 02:04:14.100
with the increase in national income

02:04:14.110 --> 02:04:16.800
per ruble is called the

02:04:16.810 --> 02:04:21.060
limit tendency to consumption.

02:04:32.310 --> 02:04:34.170
The limit tendency to consumption

02:04:34.180 --> 02:04:38.070
is equal to the increase in

02:04:38.080 --> 02:04:42.090
consumer expenses divided by the

02:04:42.100 --> 02:04:45.250
increase in income.

02:04:46.830 --> 02:04:50.530
Or it also shows how much of

02:04:50.540 --> 02:04:55.450
their additional income people consume.

02:04:55.990 --> 02:04:59.370
Well, let us suppose that the

02:04:59.380 --> 02:05:01.230
limit inclination to consumption

02:05:01.240 --> 02:05:04.830
is equal to one second delta

02:05:04.840 --> 02:05:11.250
C on the delta Y let one second.

02:05:13.190 --> 02:05:16.470
So, having received an additional

02:05:16.480 --> 02:05:19.610
income of 100 rubles, the

02:05:21.450 --> 02:05:25.030
engineers saved 50 rubles and

02:05:25.040 --> 02:05:28.590
spent 50 rubles.

02:05:29.030 --> 02:05:31.610
What consumer benefits

02:05:31.620 --> 02:05:33.750
they need.

02:05:39.250 --> 02:05:40.810
The limit of consumption

02:05:40.820 --> 02:05:42.090
is one second.

02:05:42.370 --> 02:05:43.350
Half of the extra income is

02:05:43.360 --> 02:05:45.490
spent, half is saved.

02:05:46.750 --> 02:05:49.150
So 50 rubles workers of

02:05:49.160 --> 02:05:50.970
machinery builders spent

02:05:50.980 --> 02:05:53.370
on consumer goods.

02:05:56.210 --> 02:06:01.060
For example, food industry products.

02:06:01.500 --> 02:06:02.720
What did it lead to?

02:06:04.300 --> 02:06:10.720
The demand increased by 50 rubles.

02:06:16.410 --> 02:06:19.630
In other words, the additional

02:06:19.640 --> 02:06:22.930
expenses of the working machine makers

02:06:22.940 --> 02:06:25.790
have turned into additional

02:06:25.800 --> 02:06:30.650
income of the food industry workers.

02:06:31.330 --> 02:06:34.230
What did the workers do with their income?

02:06:34.410 --> 02:06:35.670
I got another 50 rubles.

02:06:37.530 --> 02:06:39.230
We assume that the ultimate tendency

02:06:39.240 --> 02:06:40.690
to consume is the same for

02:06:40.700 --> 02:06:43.070
all, one second.

02:06:44.800 --> 02:06:47.550
So, of these 50 rubles of

02:06:47.560 --> 02:06:50.610
additional income they saved

02:06:50.620 --> 02:06:54.590
25 rubles, and spent another

02:06:54.600 --> 02:06:56.930
25, another 25 rubles.

02:06:56.940 --> 02:07:01.470
So, how much has the overall

02:07:01.480 --> 02:07:02.910
demand increased?

02:07:04.130 --> 02:07:06.150
25 rubles more.

02:07:11.040 --> 02:07:13.980
Who got those 25 rubles?

02:07:15.800 --> 02:07:18.800
Employees of those industries

02:07:18.810 --> 02:07:21.420
on the products of which the swimmers

02:07:21.430 --> 02:07:24.560
spent their additional income.

02:07:25.140 --> 02:07:28.140
Food industry workers.

02:07:28.520 --> 02:07:30.280
Workers of the food industry.

02:07:33.800 --> 02:07:36.520
What did the employees who received

02:07:36.530 --> 02:07:37.900
this income 25 rubles?

02:07:39.500 --> 02:07:41.220
Half of what we agreed,

02:07:41.760 --> 02:07:45.100
saved, half spent.

02:07:45.500 --> 02:07:48.120
So how much did the combined

02:07:48.130 --> 02:07:50.000
demand and national income increase?

02:07:53.840 --> 02:07:56.380
Another 12,5 rubles.

02:07:58.510 --> 02:07:59.290
and so on.

02:08:01.300 --> 02:08:05.260
So we have a chain.

02:08:06.560 --> 02:08:10.600
Expenditures are converted into income.

02:08:12.350 --> 02:08:16.730
Revenue is transformed into new expenses.

02:08:18.710 --> 02:08:22.170
And in the end we have a decreasing

02:08:22.180 --> 02:08:23.650
geometric progression

02:08:23.660 --> 02:08:27.050
here, plus multi-pointness, plus zero

02:08:27.390 --> 02:08:31.730
and equal will be two hundred.

02:08:34.570 --> 02:08:37.250
So, the initial demand momentum

02:08:37.260 --> 02:08:41.210
of 100 rubles resulted

02:08:41.570 --> 02:08:44.690
in a total demand and

02:08:44.700 --> 02:08:46.470
national income

02:08:46.480 --> 02:08:52.560
growth of 200 rubles.

02:08:53.360 --> 02:08:56.020
The multiplier of

02:08:56.030 --> 02:09:00.200
autonomous costs is equal

02:09:00.210 --> 02:09:01.100
to two.

02:09:01.340 --> 02:09:04.560
Look at the top formula.

02:09:04.680 --> 02:09:06.720
Multiplier is equal to what?

02:09:09.650 --> 02:09:13.650
Delta Y is divided into Delta A.

02:09:15.340 --> 02:09:18.260
Delta A is the initial change

02:09:18.270 --> 02:09:20.840
of autonomous expenses.

02:09:21.080 --> 02:09:25.380
As I said, it is 100 rubles.

02:09:27.860 --> 02:09:29.920
In the end, the total demand

02:09:29.930 --> 02:09:31.080
and national income increased

02:09:31.090 --> 02:09:32.860
by 200 rubles.

02:09:33.460 --> 02:09:34.880
So the multiplier in our example

02:09:34.890 --> 02:09:37.040
is equal to two.

02:09:41.430 --> 02:09:44.850
The multiplier can be calculated by the formula.

02:09:44.870 --> 02:09:47.850
Please look at the slide.

02:09:48.050 --> 02:09:50.270
Multiplier is equal to the unit

02:09:50.510 --> 02:09:52.450
divided by the unit, minus

02:09:52.460 --> 02:09:55.250
the limit inclination to consumption.

02:09:55.330 --> 02:09:57.010
The limit inclination to consumption

02:09:57.020 --> 02:09:58.430
in my example, as I have already

02:09:58.440 --> 02:09:59.710
told you, is equal to what?

02:10:00.390 --> 02:10:01.130
One second one.

02:10:03.070 --> 02:10:04.390
One minus one second, one second

02:10:04.400 --> 02:10:06.150
in the denominator, one divided

02:10:06.160 --> 02:10:07.250
by one second, it turned

02:10:07.390 --> 02:10:09.270
out to be two.

02:10:12.420 --> 02:10:15.120
Well, knowing the multiplier, what

02:10:15.130 --> 02:10:16.460
are we?

02:10:17.260 --> 02:10:19.640
Can we multiply it by

02:10:19.650 --> 02:10:21.440
the initial increase in autonomous

02:10:21.450 --> 02:10:23.700
costs and get what?

02:10:24.460 --> 02:10:27.920
The final increase in national

02:10:27.930 --> 02:10:29.580
income and gross domestic

02:10:29.590 --> 02:10:32.720
product.

02:10:34.500 --> 02:10:36.980
Now, let's go to the last,

02:10:36.990 --> 02:10:41.920
fifth, question of this topic.

02:10:44.260 --> 02:10:46.660
Problems of the Russian economy.

02:10:47.560 --> 02:10:49.540
Please look at the table

02:10:49.550 --> 02:10:53.520
shown on the next slide.

02:10:55.590 --> 02:10:58.930
We have years in the first line.

02:10:59.170 --> 02:11:01.610
from 92 to 2006.

02:11:02.490 --> 02:11:05.990
The second is real

02:11:06.000 --> 02:11:07.390
GDP.

02:11:09.820 --> 02:11:11.200
How is considered?

02:11:12.200 --> 02:11:15.580
The real GDP is calculated as a percentage

02:11:15.590 --> 02:11:17.040
of the previous year.

02:11:17.220 --> 02:11:20.580
The previous year is considered

02:11:20.590 --> 02:11:21.080
100.

02:11:22.660 --> 02:11:26.040
Please see what we are watching.

02:11:26.580 --> 02:11:28.260
It is 92 years.

