I have already that somewhere in one

02:14:43.050 --> 02:14:45.980
month the ruble fell, the nominal rate

02:14:45.990 --> 02:14:48.440
of the ruble fell almost three times.

02:14:51.040 --> 02:14:53.240
So the nominal rate of the ruble

02:14:56.490 --> 02:15:00.500
fell, the real rate of the ruble fell,

02:15:00.510 --> 02:15:03.720
and this led to the fact that our net

02:15:03.730 --> 02:15:05.000
exports grew.

02:15:05.980 --> 02:15:08.300
Well, remember, I said that when

02:15:08.310 --> 02:15:11.340
the real rate drops, our

02:15:11.350 --> 02:15:14.980
goods become cheaper, cheaper,

02:15:14.990 --> 02:15:19.280
cheaper relative to foreign.

02:15:22.860 --> 02:15:25.320
So, it is easier for us to export

02:15:25.330 --> 02:15:28.100
our goods, and it is harder

02:15:28.110 --> 02:15:30.600
for foreigners to import their

02:15:30.610 --> 02:15:32.640
goods to our country.

02:15:32.840 --> 02:15:34.920
Foreign goods are getting

02:15:34.930 --> 02:15:39.360
too expensive for us.

02:15:41.850 --> 02:15:43.710
But if foreign goods become

02:15:43.720 --> 02:15:45.750
too expensive, we increase

02:15:47.340 --> 02:15:49.330
demand for domestic import

02:15:49.340 --> 02:15:51.750
substitute products.

02:15:56.130 --> 02:15:59.370
So our net exports are growing.

02:15:59.970 --> 02:16:04.110
It is a component of overall demand.

02:16:04.530 --> 02:16:06.590
Let me try to explain it, maybe

02:16:06.650 --> 02:16:08.330
more clearly.

02:16:09.870 --> 02:16:12.250
Let us once again remember together

02:16:13.050 --> 02:16:16.370
which components are divided into

02:16:16.380 --> 02:16:17.630
the total demand.

02:16:32.440 --> 02:16:33.820
The four components.

02:16:34.600 --> 02:16:36.640
Consumer demand of households,

02:16:36.650 --> 02:16:39.500
investment demand of firms,

02:16:39.510 --> 02:16:43.700
demand of the state and demand

02:16:43.710 --> 02:16:47.180
of foreigners, called net exports.

02:16:47.240 --> 02:16:50.460
Net exports are the difference

02:16:50.470 --> 02:16:54.460
between our exports

02:16:54.470 --> 02:16:57.200
and imports.

02:17:05.720 --> 02:17:08.480
X exports and M imports.

02:17:09.580 --> 02:17:12.060
What happened in the

02:17:12.120 --> 02:17:15.560
August 98 crisis?

02:17:16.520 --> 02:17:19.500
Again, the ruble has fallen.

02:17:19.900 --> 02:17:22.680
The nominal rate of the ruble fell, and the

02:17:22.690 --> 02:17:24.200
real rate also fell.

02:17:24.340 --> 02:17:28.180
So our goods have been cheaper

02:17:28.190 --> 02:17:30.740
compared to foreign goods, or the same

02:17:30.750 --> 02:17:33.380
thing, foreign goods have been

02:17:33.390 --> 02:17:35.240
higher compared to our own.

02:17:40.680 --> 02:17:43.420
This makes it easier for

02:17:43.430 --> 02:17:45.040
us to export our products.

02:17:48.200 --> 02:17:48.980
Our exports have grown.

02:17:50.400 --> 02:17:53.680
On the other hand, the competitiveness

02:17:53.690 --> 02:17:55.740
of our products in relation to

02:17:55.750 --> 02:17:59.560
foreign products has increased.

02:18:00.520 --> 02:18:03.760
Foreign goods are relatively expensive.

02:18:04.420 --> 02:18:08.020
So imports have decreased.

02:18:08.800 --> 02:18:13.860
But with the decrease of imports, imports have decreased.

02:18:14.400 --> 02:18:17.320
This means that we have turned

02:18:17.330 --> 02:18:19.720
our eyes on domestic

02:18:19.730 --> 02:18:21.320
import substitute products.

02:18:21.740 --> 02:18:23.260
We have increased our demand for it.

02:18:24.700 --> 02:18:27.540
Thus, as a result of the increase

02:18:27.550 --> 02:18:31.880
in exports and the fall in imports,

02:18:31.890 --> 02:18:33.660
our net exports grew.

02:18:33.940 --> 02:18:37.240
This is a component of the overall

02:18:37.250 --> 02:18:41.840
demand for our products.

02:18:45.570 --> 02:18:49.010
The overall demand has increased.

02:18:49.670 --> 02:18:51.770
And when the overall demand increases,

02:18:51.780 --> 02:18:55.370
what do we see on the schedule?

02:18:58.730 --> 02:19:01.350
Please see the following slide.

02:19:04.830 --> 02:19:07.790
Total demand increased due

02:19:07.800 --> 02:19:09.250
to net exports.

02:19:09.670 --> 02:19:12.810
And the curve of hell is moving where?

02:19:13.930 --> 02:19:16.790
Right to AD1.

02:19:18.450 --> 02:19:21.130
What did it lead to?

02:19:21.490 --> 02:19:22.930
Prices have risen.

02:19:23.190 --> 02:19:26.030
The price level has risen from P0 to P1.

02:19:26.610 --> 02:19:28.110
But more important than another.

02:19:28.510 --> 02:19:30.770
GDP is balanced.

02:19:31.050 --> 02:19:33.230
From Y0 to Y1.

02:19:34.490 --> 02:19:37.450
So there was economic growth.

02:19:39.350 --> 02:19:41.990
Back to the table.

02:19:42.610 --> 02:19:47.950
Here we see that in 99 years, the effect

02:19:50.260 --> 02:19:52.690
of the devaluation of the ruble

02:19:52.700 --> 02:19:56.110
increased our real GDP.

02:19:56.930 --> 02:19:58.470
As they say, there would be no happiness,

02:19:58.510 --> 02:19:59.850
but misfortune helped.

02:20:00.790 --> 02:20:04.730
The financial crisis, despite all its unpleasant

02:20:04.740 --> 02:20:07.990
consequences, has led to the fact that

02:20:08.000 --> 02:20:12.110
Russia's GDP has started to grow.

02:20:12.770 --> 02:20:15.110
This is due, again, to the growth

02:20:15.120 --> 02:20:18.170
of the overall demand for our products.

02:20:18.570 --> 02:20:20.730
Many companies that previously lie

02:20:20.740 --> 02:20:23.130
in Baku suddenly found that demand

02:20:23.330 --> 02:20:26.190
for their products grew.

02:20:28.570 --> 02:20:32.010
Again, I repeat, the curve of AD has

02:20:32.020 --> 02:20:37.440
shifted to the right and the balanced

02:20:37.450 --> 02:20:39.160
GDP has grown.

02:20:44.040 --> 02:20:47.440
In the second half of 1999 the

02:20:47.450 --> 02:20:53.520
growth of GDP continued.

02:20:53.960 --> 02:20:55.080
Look at the table.

02:20:55.720 --> 02:21:01.780
In 2000, GDP grew by 10% compared

02:21:01.790 --> 02:21:02.720
to 1999.

02:21:03.180 --> 02:21:04.880
Remember, we take

02:21:04.890 --> 02:21:06.480
100 each year.

02:21:10.820 --> 02:21:15.220
Now the multiplier effect works.

02:21:19.660 --> 02:21:21.560
Remember I just explained it?

02:21:21.700 --> 02:21:22.820
The multiplier effect.

02:21:23.860 --> 02:21:24.760
What is he expressing?

02:21:24.770 --> 02:21:25.980
Let's, in this case.

02:21:28.420 --> 02:21:31.700
Our net exports have increased.

02:21:33.020 --> 02:21:35.640
Our companies have found that there

02:21:35.650 --> 02:21:37.840
is a demand for their products.

02:21:39.120 --> 02:21:40.900
But if demand for their products

02:21:40.910 --> 02:21:44.120
grew, and they began to produce more

02:21:44.130 --> 02:21:46.340
products, the incomes of those

02:21:46.350 --> 02:21:48.780
who produce these products increased

02:21:48.790 --> 02:21:50.980
accordingly.

02:21:51.340 --> 02:21:53.600
Income increased, what increased?

02:21:54.560 --> 02:21:55.160
their expenses.

02:21:56.220 --> 02:21:58.100
Remember the multiplier effect?

02:21:59.300 --> 02:22:01.020
Growth in expenses causes growth in

02:22:01.030 --> 02:22:03.340
income, growth in income causes growth

02:22:03.350 --> 02:22:05.100
in expenses.

02:22:05.540 --> 02:22:06.860
New growth of expenses.

02:22:07.060 --> 02:22:09.840
So what have we started to observe?

02:22:10.720 --> 02:22:13.680
Due to the increase in incomes, consumer

02:22:13.690 --> 02:22:15.860
expenses have increased.

02:22:16.360 --> 02:22:19.820
The companies have seen the demand for their products

02:22:19.830 --> 02:22:20.620
increase.

02:22:21.740 --> 02:22:23.280
What will this demand say?

02:22:23.290 --> 02:22:26.220
They began to expand, buy

02:22:26.230 --> 02:22:27.400
new equipment, that is,

02:22:27.410 --> 02:22:32.260
to make investment expenses.

02:22:32.320 --> 02:22:34.020
So what component has increased

02:22:34.030 --> 02:22:35.820
the overall demand?

02:22:37.220 --> 02:22:38.240
The Investment.

02:22:39.660 --> 02:22:43.640
So the overall demand has increased even more.

02:22:44.700 --> 02:22:48.300
And the curve of the total demand,

02:22:48.310 --> 02:22:54.080
see the next slide, it shifted even

02:22:54.090 --> 02:22:56.700
more from the position of AD1,

02:22:56.710 --> 02:22:59.460
on the previous slide we had

02:22:59.470 --> 02:23:01.800
AD1, already in the position

02:23:01.810 --> 02:23:03.880
of AD2.

02:23:07.820 --> 02:23:09.940
And what have we come to?

02:23:12.900 --> 02:23:17.240
We have come to the fact that the balanced

02:23:17.250 --> 02:23:22.620
GDP has reached the potential level.

02:23:22.760 --> 02:23:24.440
Look again.

02:23:24.860 --> 02:23:27.620
Function of total demand.

02:23:28.720 --> 02:23:30.580
She is constantly moving to the right.

02:23:30.640 --> 02:23:32.900
It has adopted the AD2.

02:23:34.900 --> 02:23:37.360
And now it crosses the

02:23:37.370 --> 02:23:39.560
long-term curve of total supply

02:23:39.570 --> 02:23:43.860
at point E2.

02:23:44.200 --> 02:23:47.460
This means that the balanced GDP

02:23:47.470 --> 02:23:49.840
has reached a potential level.

02:23:51.240 --> 02:23:53.440
Let us go back to the table again.

02:23:55.500 --> 02:23:59.020
Look at 90...

02:23:59.030 --> 02:24:01.080
by 2002.

02:24:02.540 --> 02:24:06.820
At the end of the year, economists

02:24:06.830 --> 02:24:08.700
were very pessimistic.

02:24:09.260 --> 02:24:11.960
They said the growth was out.

02:24:14.280 --> 02:24:19.780
In 2000, GDP grew by 10%.

02:24:19.790 --> 02:24:25.340
In 2001, GDP grew by 5.1%.

02:24:25.350 --> 02:24:31.400
In 2002, it increased by 4.7%.

02:24:31.410 --> 02:24:34.880
Economists have predicted that

02:24:34.890 --> 02:24:36.900
growth will soon stop.

02:24:38.100 --> 02:24:39.400
From what did they come?

02:24:40.500 --> 02:24:43.100
They assumed that the balanced

02:24:43.110 --> 02:24:45.980
GDP had already reached

02:24:45.990 --> 02:24:47.560
the potential level.

02:24:48.280 --> 02:24:50.520
And I explained that when

02:24:50.530 --> 02:24:52.980
the balanced GDP reaches a

02:24:52.990 --> 02:24:56.080
potential level, further growth in

02:24:56.090 --> 02:24:59.280
the aggregate demand leads only

02:24:59.290 --> 02:25:02.980
to growth in production only in

02:25:02.990 --> 02:25:04.620
a short period of time.

02:25:04.900 --> 02:25:06.780
In the long run, as the economy

02:25:06.790 --> 02:25:08.080
is overloaded, prices start

02:25:08.600 --> 02:25:10.940
to rise and the economy

02:25:10.950 --> 02:25:12.280
returns to potential

02:25:12.290 --> 02:25:14.460
GDP only at higher

02:25:14.470 --> 02:25:15.600
price levels.

