where the investment climate is very good,

02:30:10.780 --> 02:30:15.320
and private investment does not

02:30:15.330 --> 02:30:19.540
grow so that it is significant, but

02:30:19.550 --> 02:30:22.020
the investment can be made by the state.

02:30:24.260 --> 02:30:26.640
It would seem that the result would be the same.

02:30:27.300 --> 02:30:28.500
High investment and high

02:30:28.510 --> 02:30:29.320
economic growth.

02:30:30.060 --> 02:30:32.920
But experience shows that

02:30:34.410 --> 02:30:36.980
this outcome is relatively

02:30:36.990 --> 02:30:39.460
short-term, for the simple

02:30:39.470 --> 02:30:43.400
reason that the state

02:30:43.410 --> 02:30:49.140
is initially a bad entrepreneur.

02:30:50.200 --> 02:30:52.440
It spends money badly.

02:30:52.640 --> 02:30:55.060
Most often not as efficient as

02:30:55.070 --> 02:30:56.260
the private sector does.

02:30:57.740 --> 02:30:59.920
Public investments are usually less

02:30:59.930 --> 02:31:02.660
efficient than private investments.

02:31:03.900 --> 02:31:06.500
Economic growth in such conditions

02:31:06.510 --> 02:31:09.700
is unlikely to be sustainable.

02:31:10.380 --> 02:31:11.660
And what?

02:31:12.140 --> 02:31:13.580
Let us talk a little bit

02:31:13.590 --> 02:31:15.400
about inflation.

02:31:16.100 --> 02:31:18.280
Let us go back to our

02:31:18.290 --> 02:31:19.420
table.

02:31:20.100 --> 02:31:22.660
Inflation means price increases.

02:31:23.980 --> 02:31:25.160
The overall price increase.

02:31:26.000 --> 02:31:28.000
What are we watching?

02:31:28.320 --> 02:31:32.500
Well, at least in the 2000s,

02:31:34.220 --> 02:31:36.320
inflation, fortunately,

02:31:36.330 --> 02:31:38.960
has slowed down.

02:31:40.080 --> 02:31:41.860
Why this happens?

02:31:44.100 --> 02:31:46.320
To do this, we need to discuss

02:31:47.400 --> 02:31:50.140
the question of what causes

02:31:50.150 --> 02:31:51.460
inflation.

02:31:52.880 --> 02:31:54.880
Please look at the slide.

02:31:55.800 --> 02:31:58.660
There are three causes of inflation,

02:31:59.360 --> 02:32:01.620
respectively, three types of inflation.

02:32:04.370 --> 02:32:05.830
The first type of inflation.

02:32:07.330 --> 02:32:10.790
This is inflation caused by increased demand.

02:32:10.800 --> 02:32:14.910
Prices are rising because

02:32:14.920 --> 02:32:16.950
the overall demand is increasing.

02:32:21.600 --> 02:32:26.980
The curve of hell is shifting to the right.

02:32:27.160 --> 02:32:29.020
The curve of hell moves to the right.

02:32:29.720 --> 02:32:32.560
Graphically, how can this be shown?

02:32:40.120 --> 02:32:41.920
The common model is the total

02:32:41.930 --> 02:32:44.000
supply, the total demand.

02:32:44.680 --> 02:32:48.000
The combined demand function, yes,

02:32:48.010 --> 02:32:52.220
and the short-term combined supply function.

02:32:54.160 --> 02:32:57.730
There is a level of P0 price

02:32:57.740 --> 02:33:02.390
balance.

02:33:03.170 --> 02:33:04.790
The overall demand is growing.

02:33:07.230 --> 02:33:08.650
What happens on the schedule when

02:33:08.660 --> 02:33:09.530
the overall demand grows?

02:33:12.090 --> 02:33:14.270
The combined demand curve, as I have

02:33:14.280 --> 02:33:18.330
already, is shifting to the right to the

02:33:18.340 --> 02:33:20.490
AD1 position.

02:33:25.200 --> 02:33:26.880
What are we watching?

02:33:28.000 --> 02:33:31.880
Prices are starting to rise.

02:33:34.140 --> 02:33:37.410
That is, the increase in total demand causes

02:33:37.420 --> 02:33:40.330
price increases, that is, inflation.

02:33:41.430 --> 02:33:44.230
Usually, this growth in total demand

02:33:44.240 --> 02:33:49.010
is due most often to either an

02:33:49.020 --> 02:33:50.050
increase in public spending or

02:33:50.060 --> 02:33:54.410
to the growth of the money mass in

02:33:54.420 --> 02:33:55.230
the economy.

02:33:55.750 --> 02:33:58.150
The central bank prints more money, the money

02:33:58.830 --> 02:34:01.550
mass grows, the total demand grows, the

02:34:01.560 --> 02:34:03.670
curve of the value of the currency

02:34:03.680 --> 02:34:07.070
moves to the right, prices start to rise.

02:34:07.390 --> 02:34:09.270
This is the first type of inflation.

02:34:11.290 --> 02:34:13.450
The second type of inflation, look at

02:34:13.460 --> 02:34:17.910
the slide, is inflation caused

02:34:17.920 --> 02:34:19.710
by rising costs.

02:34:21.690 --> 02:34:24.370
Prices are rising because

02:34:24.380 --> 02:34:26.650
the costs of producers are increasing.

02:34:29.580 --> 02:34:32.900
When the cost increases, what happens?

02:34:44.990 --> 02:34:47.310
Where is the short-term curve of

02:34:47.320 --> 02:34:48.990
the total offer shifting?

02:34:52.090 --> 02:34:53.310
up to.

02:34:53.630 --> 02:34:55.150
What are we watching?

02:34:59.990 --> 02:35:00.870
Again, the rise of prices.

02:35:06.740 --> 02:35:08.400
This is the most unpleasant situation

02:35:08.410 --> 02:35:09.980
in the economy.

02:35:10.280 --> 02:35:12.600
This is called stackflation.

02:35:14.120 --> 02:35:18.820
This is when price growth is accompanied

02:35:18.830 --> 02:35:23.400
by a fall in GDP.

02:35:23.410 --> 02:35:27.040
Costs for producers are increasing.

02:35:27.620 --> 02:35:30.520
With the previous combined demand,

02:35:33.130 --> 02:35:36.370
the balance GDP decreases.

02:35:37.710 --> 02:35:41.610
This inflation is most often caused by

02:35:41.620 --> 02:35:44.410
the rise in prices of the main types

02:35:44.420 --> 02:35:46.450
of production resources.

02:35:47.070 --> 02:35:51.510
For example, RAO Railways increased tariffs

02:35:51.520 --> 02:35:53.550
for freight transportation.

02:35:53.890 --> 02:35:57.330
Gazprom has raised gas prices.

02:35:58.210 --> 02:36:02.650
The EU has raised electricity tariffs.

02:36:02.790 --> 02:36:07.370
The costs of companies are rising, and they are

02:36:07.380 --> 02:36:10.630
forced to raise prices in response.

02:36:10.890 --> 02:36:12.910
There is inflation caused by the

02:36:12.920 --> 02:36:14.390
increase in costs.

02:36:15.050 --> 02:36:17.930
And finally, the third type of inflation

02:36:17.940 --> 02:36:22.530
is inflation caused by inflation expectations.

02:36:22.540 --> 02:36:27.820
Prices are rising here because both

02:36:27.830 --> 02:36:30.760
producers and consumers expect

02:36:30.770 --> 02:36:33.040
their growth.

02:36:35.770 --> 02:36:37.810
Look what an interesting thing.

02:36:41.010 --> 02:36:42.710
Expectation is a psychological factor.

02:36:44.230 --> 02:36:47.150
In economics, psychology has

02:36:47.160 --> 02:36:48.110
material power.

02:36:49.390 --> 02:36:52.690
If you expect something, it will

02:36:52.700 --> 02:36:54.030
definitely happen.

02:36:54.750 --> 02:36:56.970
And so with inflation.

02:36:57.350 --> 02:37:01.810
If everyone expects inflation,

02:37:01.820 --> 02:37:03.170
prices will rise.

02:37:03.490 --> 02:37:05.170
Why can this happen?

02:37:06.590 --> 02:37:09.590
Well, imagine, the company

02:37:09.600 --> 02:37:13.010
plans, makes a price list for

02:37:13.020 --> 02:37:14.490
next year.

02:37:18.370 --> 02:37:22.050
And it expects prices to rise

02:37:22.060 --> 02:37:24.130
by about 10 percent next year.

02:37:24.140 --> 02:37:24.670


02:37:24.810 --> 02:37:27.110
He doesn't know, but he can expect.

02:37:27.290 --> 02:37:29.070
There are certain inflationary

02:37:29.080 --> 02:37:30.190
expectations.

02:37:30.490 --> 02:37:31.270
What will she do?

02:37:32.130 --> 02:37:35.070
It will definitely put its inflation

02:37:35.080 --> 02:37:36.910
expectations in its

02:37:36.920 --> 02:37:38.650
vacation prices.

02:37:39.310 --> 02:37:41.270
If all companies do this, expectations

02:37:41.280 --> 02:37:42.670
will become reality.

02:37:42.850 --> 02:37:44.550
Prices will really rise.

02:37:46.430 --> 02:37:48.550
That is the danger of inflation.

02:37:48.930 --> 02:37:50.630
Inflation can be prolonged because

02:37:51.310 --> 02:37:53.490
existing inflation generates

02:37:53.500 --> 02:37:55.390
inflation expectations.

02:37:55.870 --> 02:37:58.050
Inflation expectations are

02:37:58.060 --> 02:37:59.550
contributing to new inflation.

02:37:59.950 --> 02:38:01.470
And so it can continue for a long time.

02:38:03.170 --> 02:38:04.550
It is difficult to fight inflation.

02:38:04.630 --> 02:38:07.990
We need to overcome inflation expectations.

02:38:09.210 --> 02:38:10.810
And look at.

02:38:10.850 --> 02:38:14.170
I would like to go back to

02:38:14.180 --> 02:38:20.120
illustrate the causes of inflation

02:38:20.130 --> 02:38:23.740
to the equation of quantitative

02:38:23.750 --> 02:38:25.200
money theory known to us.

02:38:26.960 --> 02:38:28.240
That I explained in the first question

02:38:28.250 --> 02:38:30.220
of this topic.

02:38:43.210 --> 02:38:44.470
M, V, P and Y

02:38:47.000 --> 02:38:49.500
Let us rewrite this equation.

02:38:49.940 --> 02:38:51.020
This is this way.

02:38:53.290 --> 02:38:59.710
p is equal to m, v, divided by y.

02:39:05.680 --> 02:39:06.780
What is on the left?

02:39:08.160 --> 02:39:09.340
The level of prices.

02:39:10.120 --> 02:39:11.300
In the right side.

02:39:11.980 --> 02:39:14.860
The rest is what the price level

02:39:14.870 --> 02:39:15.500
depends on.

02:39:16.300 --> 02:39:18.640
A change in price level is inflation.

02:39:19.620 --> 02:39:21.100
Why can prices rise?

02:39:21.140 --> 02:39:23.660
Please look at the equation.

02:39:25.280 --> 02:39:25.840
Why then?

02:39:26.920 --> 02:39:30.500
Prices can rise because of growth,

02:39:30.510 --> 02:39:32.500
what?

02:39:32.780 --> 02:39:34.480
Money in the economy.

02:39:35.380 --> 02:39:37.140
The central bank printed more money than

02:39:37.180 --> 02:39:37.980
needed.

02:39:40.190 --> 02:39:41.810
The money mass has grown.

02:39:41.820 --> 02:39:45.450
And with the other equals, prices start to rise.

02:39:46.290 --> 02:39:48.130
This is a typical inflation caused by increased

02:39:48.140 --> 02:39:49.750
demand.

02:39:50.230 --> 02:39:51.690
Why can prices rise?

02:39:54.700 --> 02:39:58.580
Prices may rise because real

02:39:58.590 --> 02:40:00.680
GDP is falling.

02:40:01.200 --> 02:40:02.560
The goods are becoming less in the

02:40:02.570 --> 02:40:04.100
economy, and the money is still

02:40:04.110 --> 02:40:05.380
the same.

02:40:06.320 --> 02:40:08.820
So the former amount of money is

02:40:08.830 --> 02:40:10.320
chased for fewer goods, and prices

02:40:10.330 --> 02:40:12.320
are beginning to rise again.

02:40:13.620 --> 02:40:16.920
This is inflation caused by rising costs.

02:40:17.060 --> 02:40:17.460
Why is?

02:40:17.820 --> 02:40:19.920
Because with the increase of costs,

02:40:19.930 --> 02:40:21.700
production usually decreases.

02:40:23.080 --> 02:40:26.180
Why can prices still

02:40:26.190 --> 02:40:27.020
rise?

02:40:27.900 --> 02:40:32.680
The speed of money circulation increases.

02:40:42.130 --> 02:40:45.250
And this can actually be both inflation

02:40:45.260 --> 02:40:47.210
caused by rising demand and inflation

02:40:47.350 --> 02:40:48.370
caused by inflation

02:40:48.380 --> 02:40:50.150
expectations.

02:40:50.160 --> 02:40:51.210
And that expectation?

02:40:51.220 --> 02:40:52.090
See also.

02:40:52.730 --> 02:40:56.330
You get a salary and expect prices

02:40:56.340 --> 02:40:59.250
to rise soon.

02:41:01.770 --> 02:41:03.130
How will you behave?

02:41:03.170 --> 02:41:04.130
What will you do?

02:41:05.770 --> 02:41:09.130
You will try to get the

02:41:09.140 --> 02:41:11.130
money you get.

02:41:11.350 --> 02:41:12.730
Something to spend.

02:41:13.350 --> 02:41:15.250
Do not leave them at home, otherwise

02:41:15.260 --> 02:41:16.510
they will be dishonored.

02:41:18.710 --> 02:41:20.350
The one who gets your money, what

02:41:20.360 --> 02:41:21.350
will he do?

02:41:21.550 --> 02:41:22.210
The same thing.

02:41:23.150 --> 02:41:25.870
People will spend money faster.

02:41:26.430 --> 02:41:29.050
The speed of money circulation will increase

02:41:29.060 --> 02:41:30.870
and prices will start to affect.

02:41:36.640 --> 02:41:39.760
Why is inflation slowing

02:41:39.770 --> 02:41:41.240
down?

02:41:45.420 --> 02:41:49.000
On the one hand, it would seem,

02:41:49.340 --> 02:41:51.340
if you look at the statistics, the

02:41:51.350 --> 02:41:54.020
money mass is growing in our

02:41:54.030 --> 02:41:55.320
savings quite quickly.

02:41:59.380 --> 02:42:03.300
But the central bank, together with

02:42:03.310 --> 02:42:05.600
the government, is said to

02:42:06.080 --> 02:42:09.320
be bound by excess money or, as

02:42:09.330 --> 02:42:12.400
they say, sterilizing excess liquidity.

02:42:16.900 --> 02:42:19.400
This will result in the

02:42:19.410 --> 02:42:22.240
slowing of the money flow.

02:42:24.010 --> 02:42:28.050
In addition, the factor that inhibits

02:42:32.370 --> 02:42:36.900
inflation is the moderate increase

02:42:36.910 --> 02:42:39.060
in tariffs of so-called

02:42:39.070 --> 02:42:42.830
natural monopolies – Gazprom, RAO

02:42:42.840 --> 02:42:45.350
EU, RAO RZD.

02:42:46.810 --> 02:42:49.630
This leads to the fact that the costs of

02:42:49.640 --> 02:42:51.450
firms are growing quite moderately, which

02:42:53.960 --> 02:42:55.640
also does not contribute to inflation.

02:42:57.020 --> 02:42:59.740
And finally, a very important

02:42:59.750 --> 02:43:02.160
anti-inflationary factor is that

02:43:02.170 --> 02:43:05.460
people have not formed any

02:43:05.470 --> 02:43:07.480
serious inflationary expectations

02:43:07.490 --> 02:43:09.260
in the economy.

02:43:11.660 --> 02:43:14.880
And since inflation expectations

02:43:17.880 --> 02:43:21.200
are low, the rate of money circulation

02:43:22.810 --> 02:43:25.860
will also be low, which contributes

02:43:25.870 --> 02:43:30.680
to the slowing up of price growth.

02:43:32.630 --> 02:43:35.610
There is another very interesting question

02:43:37.580 --> 02:43:40.170
related to monetary policy, the

02:43:40.180 --> 02:43:42.990
connection of inflation with

02:43:43.000 --> 02:43:46.310
the monetary policy of the Central Bank.

