03:01:45.570 --> 03:01:47.480
are included in the state budget often

03:01:47.490 --> 03:01:48.320
not because they are really needed,

03:01:48.330 --> 03:01:52.820
but because they are done year

03:01:52.830 --> 03:01:53.700
after year.

03:01:54.180 --> 03:01:56.640
Or because certain lobbyists

03:01:56.650 --> 03:02:00.100
manage to break through these costs.

03:02:02.610 --> 03:02:04.530
This is on the one hand, and on

03:02:04.540 --> 03:02:06.890
the other hand, when the money is

03:02:06.900 --> 03:02:08.430
allocated for a particular item

03:02:08.440 --> 03:02:11.690
of expenditure, it is often spent

03:02:11.700 --> 03:02:13.670
inefficiently.

03:02:16.420 --> 03:02:19.800
In the case of the inefficiency

03:02:19.810 --> 03:02:23.280
of public spending, I would like

03:02:23.290 --> 03:02:30.200
to give you this matrix, which

03:02:30.740 --> 03:02:34.520
was made by the famous,

03:02:34.540 --> 03:02:36.920
recently deceased American economist,

03:02:36.930 --> 03:02:38.880
Nobel Prize laureate Milton

03:02:38.890 --> 03:02:40.660
Friedman.

03:02:42.960 --> 03:02:44.640
The Friedman Matrix.

03:02:45.600 --> 03:02:46.960
What does Friedman come from?

03:02:47.540 --> 03:02:51.080
Money is yours and money

03:02:51.090 --> 03:02:54.420
is someone else's.

03:02:55.060 --> 03:02:57.540
On the other hand, money can

03:02:57.550 --> 03:03:00.440
be spent for yourself, and

03:03:00.450 --> 03:03:02.300
money can be spent for

03:03:02.310 --> 03:03:03.120
others.

03:03:04.120 --> 03:03:06.440
This is the construction of the matrix.

03:03:21.280 --> 03:03:22.800
The four segments.

03:03:23.800 --> 03:03:32.200
Here is my money, here is the money of others.

03:03:43.490 --> 03:03:46.590
Here for yourself, here for

03:03:46.600 --> 03:03:50.100
others.

03:03:58.040 --> 03:04:01.540
What do individuals, households

03:04:01.550 --> 03:04:03.820
or companies spend?

03:04:06.350 --> 03:04:08.650
Money for yourself.

03:04:10.310 --> 03:04:12.090
When you get some income, you spend

03:04:12.450 --> 03:04:14.090
it for yourself and your family

03:04:14.100 --> 03:04:15.830
members, and you spend

03:04:15.840 --> 03:04:17.070
your money.

03:04:17.870 --> 03:04:21.070
In this case, spending

03:04:21.080 --> 03:04:24.190
is done in the best way, the

03:04:24.710 --> 03:04:26.050
most rational way.

03:04:27.710 --> 03:04:31.170
You may be spending your

03:04:31.180 --> 03:04:34.830
money on others.

03:04:37.030 --> 03:04:38.170
When is it possible?

03:04:41.160 --> 03:04:44.580
For example, you buy someone

03:04:44.590 --> 03:04:45.960
a birthday present.

03:04:47.680 --> 03:04:49.920
You spend your money on someone

03:04:49.930 --> 03:04:50.740
else.

03:04:52.080 --> 03:04:53.760
Are you interested in what here?

03:04:55.300 --> 03:04:56.500
At least not to

03:04:56.510 --> 03:04:58.380
spend too much.

03:04:59.640 --> 03:05:03.020
But often you are not so selected about the

03:05:03.030 --> 03:05:05.060
quality of the purchase, because you

03:05:05.070 --> 03:05:06.340
are spending not for yourself.

03:05:07.960 --> 03:05:10.360
Here, the money is not spent as effectively

03:05:10.370 --> 03:05:11.720
as in the first quadrant,

03:05:11.730 --> 03:05:15.100
in the first segment.

03:05:15.400 --> 03:05:17.880
What other option is possible?

03:05:18.400 --> 03:05:23.580
You can spend other people's money for

03:05:23.590 --> 03:05:24.500
yourself.

03:05:27.200 --> 03:05:29.060
When do you do it?

03:05:32.980 --> 03:05:38.830
For example, when you eat lunch at the

03:05:38.840 --> 03:05:39.930
company.

03:05:41.790 --> 03:05:43.350
What are you interested in here?

03:05:44.390 --> 03:05:48.650
To get the best set of benefits,

03:05:48.660 --> 03:05:50.950
but you are not interested

03:05:50.960 --> 03:05:53.590
in rational spending of

03:05:53.600 --> 03:05:54.550
money at all.

03:05:57.360 --> 03:05:59.800
You are not interested in saving

03:05:59.810 --> 03:06:02.500
money as much as possible.

03:06:02.510 --> 03:06:03.720
Money is not yours.

03:06:04.860 --> 03:06:07.960
And finally, the worst situation, when?

03:06:12.120 --> 03:06:15.560
When you spend someone else's money

03:06:15.570 --> 03:06:16.320
for others.

03:06:17.960 --> 03:06:19.180
Who does this?

03:06:20.220 --> 03:06:22.120
Who spends other people's money?

03:06:23.840 --> 03:06:24.860
