03:08:04.460 --> 03:08:06.940
Budgetary and fiscal policy

03:08:06.950 --> 03:08:09.560
and macroeconomic regulation.

03:08:10.640 --> 03:08:12.860
From the point of view of macroeconomics,

03:08:12.870 --> 03:08:14.980
budgetary and tax policy

03:08:14.990 --> 03:08:18.220
is a set of measures of the

03:08:18.230 --> 03:08:22.120
state to change the state's

03:08:22.130 --> 03:08:24.560
expenditure and taxes to

03:08:24.570 --> 03:08:27.140
potential GDP and overcome

03:08:27.150 --> 03:08:29.480
inflation.

03:08:30.100 --> 03:08:32.200
In other words, the state

03:08:33.630 --> 03:08:36.600
strives to ensure that the economy

03:08:36.610 --> 03:08:38.620
works at full capacity and

03:08:38.630 --> 03:08:41.420
that prices do not rise.

03:08:41.720 --> 03:08:44.780
There is a distinction

03:08:44.790 --> 03:08:47.560
between budgetary and tax policy.

03:08:48.120 --> 03:08:50.080
Please look at the slide.

03:08:50.660 --> 03:08:52.680
The purpose of a budgetary tax policy

03:08:52.690 --> 03:08:56.220
is to overcome the cyclical recession

03:08:56.230 --> 03:08:58.380
of the economy, when the

03:08:58.660 --> 03:09:01.620
GDP is actually less than

03:09:01.630 --> 03:09:02.940
the potential.

03:09:04.300 --> 03:09:07.140
And it involves increasing

03:09:07.150 --> 03:09:09.640
public spending or tax

03:09:09.650 --> 03:09:12.900
cuts, or a combination of

03:09:12.910 --> 03:09:13.440
these.

03:09:15.480 --> 03:09:18.500
It is clear that when we increase

03:09:18.820 --> 03:09:20.460
public spending, public

03:09:20.660 --> 03:09:21.680
spending is a component

03:09:21.690 --> 03:09:24.920
of the total demand.

03:09:24.930 --> 03:09:26.020
Accordingly, the increase in

03:09:26.030 --> 03:09:27.760
public spending leads to the fact

03:09:27.770 --> 03:09:30.300
that the overall demand is growing.

03:09:32.220 --> 03:09:34.920
GDP is also growing.

03:09:38.680 --> 03:09:40.640
Please look at the schedule

03:09:40.650 --> 03:09:42.420
on the slide.

