After all, if the state increases

03:10:52.360 --> 03:10:55.290
its expenses with this income,

03:10:55.310 --> 03:10:57.490
with this national income, then this

03:10:57.500 --> 03:11:00.510
is autonomous expenses.

03:11:01.570 --> 03:11:03.570
And we have already talked with

03:11:04.210 --> 03:11:06.970
you that in the end, the balance

03:11:06.980 --> 03:11:09.550
of GDP and national

03:11:10.030 --> 03:11:13.050
income increase by a greater

03:11:13.060 --> 03:11:14.770
amount than the initial

03:11:14.780 --> 03:11:15.790
change in public spending

03:11:15.800 --> 03:11:19.710
due to the multiplier effect.

03:11:20.550 --> 03:11:22.670
The multiplier effect I have explained

03:11:22.680 --> 03:11:24.350
to you once.

03:11:24.510 --> 03:11:26.210
For example, if you remember

03:11:26.220 --> 03:11:28.450
the company's investment costs.

03:11:28.830 --> 03:11:30.670
The same effect is also effective

03:11:30.680 --> 03:11:35.250
when the state increases its spending.

03:11:36.650 --> 03:11:39.870
Please look at the slide.

03:11:40.410 --> 03:11:42.870
What is the multiplier effect?

03:11:43.110 --> 03:11:46.150
What is the increase in national

03:11:46.160 --> 03:11:47.750
income?

03:11:48.290 --> 03:11:50.410
The increase in public expenditure

03:11:50.570 --> 03:11:52.850
multiplied by the multiplier

03:11:52.860 --> 03:11:55.570
of public autonomous expenditure.

03:11:56.990 --> 03:11:59.070
And again I want to remind you that

03:11:59.080 --> 03:12:01.390
the multiplier of autonomous costs

03:12:01.400 --> 03:12:05.330
is calculated by the formula known to you.

03:12:05.450 --> 03:12:07.790
Multiplier is equal to a unit

03:12:08.030 --> 03:12:10.050
divided by one, minus the

03:12:10.060 --> 03:12:11.550
limit inclination to consumption.

03:12:12.430 --> 03:12:14.170
Another way of conducting

03:12:14.180 --> 03:12:17.430
a budgetary-tax policy

03:12:19.950 --> 03:12:24.720
is to reduce taxes.

03:12:26.540 --> 03:12:28.260
The state does not increase its

03:12:28.270 --> 03:12:30.480
expenses, but reduces taxes

03:12:30.490 --> 03:12:33.400
in the expectation that

03:12:33.410 --> 03:12:35.900
people will have additional funds

03:12:36.380 --> 03:12:38.360
that they will use to increase

03:12:38.370 --> 03:12:40.940
the overall demand, which will

03:12:40.950 --> 03:12:43.620
again stimulate the economy.

03:12:49.750 --> 03:12:56.090
In this case, the same thing,

03:12:56.230 --> 03:12:58.190
look, you can go back to the old

03:12:58.200 --> 03:13:00.650
schedule, in this case, also the

03:13:00.660 --> 03:13:02.970
reduction of taxes leads to the

03:13:02.980 --> 03:13:04.450
fact that people have more money,

03:13:04.460 --> 03:13:05.930
household people have more money,

03:13:05.940 --> 03:13:08.050
and they can increase

03:13:08.060 --> 03:13:11.030
their expenses.

03:13:11.090 --> 03:13:16.210
Accordingly, the curve of the

03:13:16.220 --> 03:13:19.650
AD shifts to the right, and the balance

03:13:19.660 --> 03:13:22.270
WOP becomes equal to the potential.

03:13:23.510 --> 03:13:25.370
To avoid misunderstandings, I want

03:13:25.380 --> 03:13:30.630
to explain that reducing taxes does

03:13:30.640 --> 03:13:32.030
not mean reducing government spending

03:13:32.040 --> 03:13:33.930
at the same time.

03:13:35.580 --> 03:13:37.060
The government reduces taxes

03:13:37.070 --> 03:13:41.080
but does not reduce spending.

03:13:41.460 --> 03:13:42.680
If it reduced its costs,

03:13:42.690 --> 03:13:45.120
then there would be no stimulating

03:13:45.130 --> 03:13:45.880
effect.

03:13:46.600 --> 03:13:49.300
The state keeps its expenses the

03:13:49.310 --> 03:13:56.360
same, but reduces taxes.

03:13:57.800 --> 03:13:59.860
The disadvantage of such

03:14:01.910 --> 03:14:04.560
a policy is that it can lead

03:14:04.570 --> 03:14:06.940
to a deficit of

03:14:06.950 --> 03:14:08.840
the state budget.

03:14:12.600 --> 03:14:16.060
The deficit of the state budget

03:14:16.070 --> 03:14:22.340
has a negative impact on the economy.

03:14:22.520 --> 03:14:24.200
Especially if he is big.

03:14:24.210 --> 03:14:26.320
The budget deficit is considered

03:14:26.330 --> 03:14:29.580
to exceed 3% of gross domestic

03:14:29.590 --> 03:14:30.780
product.

03:14:30.790 --> 03:14:31.460
That is much.

03:14:33.320 --> 03:14:35.260
Why is the state budget deficit

03:14:35.270 --> 03:14:36.160
bad?

03:14:37.060 --> 03:14:38.700
What is wrong with everything he does?

03:14:43.740 --> 03:14:48.400
If there is a deficit,

03:14:48.410 --> 03:14:54.020
the deficit must be covered.

03:14:55.060 --> 03:14:56.520
How can it be covered?

03:14:57.120 --> 03:14:59.740
You can print extra money.

03:15:00.840 --> 03:15:02.500
This threatens inflation.

03:15:03.880 --> 03:15:06.400
The government often covers the

03:15:06.410 --> 03:15:10.380
budget deficit with loans in the

03:15:10.390 --> 03:15:11.540
financial markets.

03:15:12.020 --> 03:15:13.280
If the government has a

03:15:13.290 --> 03:15:16.700
deficit, it must be borrowed.

03:15:16.980 --> 03:15:19.640
But when such a large borrower enters

03:15:19.650 --> 03:15:23.820
the market, this leads to the fact

03:15:24.760 --> 03:15:27.820
that the price of the loan, namely

03:15:27.830 --> 03:15:30.780
the interest rate, begins to rise.

03:15:32.600 --> 03:15:35.460
And if you remember, investment costs

03:15:35.470 --> 03:15:40.740
of firms and household expenses,

03:15:40.750 --> 03:15:44.200
they are related to interest rate.

03:15:44.940 --> 03:15:47.980
When interest rates rise, business

03:15:48.860 --> 03:15:50.960
investments and household

03:15:50.970 --> 03:15:52.860
consumer spending decrease.

03:15:54.600 --> 03:15:58.120
This phenomenon is called the macroeconomic

03:15:58.130 --> 03:16:00.220
suppression effect.

03:16:00.460 --> 03:16:05.340
That is, if we cut taxes without cutting

03:16:06.540 --> 03:16:08.380
government spending, we will face

03:16:08.390 --> 03:16:11.500
the fact that because of the rise in interest

03:16:11.510 --> 03:16:14.420
rates, investment costs of firms will

03:16:14.430 --> 03:16:17.840
be reduced and partially negative consequences

03:16:17.850 --> 03:16:22.280
will be caused by the increase

03:16:22.290 --> 03:16:27.700
in interest rates.

03:16:27.710 --> 03:16:30.660
This may also partly lead to the

03:16:30.670 --> 03:16:34.000
fact that household expenses will

03:16:34.010 --> 03:16:36.380
not grow so much due to the rise

03:16:36.390 --> 03:16:39.360
in interest rates.

03:16:39.600 --> 03:16:41.680
Well, by the way, the same effect

03:16:41.690 --> 03:16:45.580
will be when the state increases

03:16:45.590 --> 03:16:47.580
its spending without increasing

03:16:47.590 --> 03:16:49.300
taxes.

03:16:49.520 --> 03:16:51.800
The budget deficit also has the

03:16:51.810 --> 03:16:55.320
same negative consequences.

03:16:58.120 --> 03:17:02.160
Well, and if we talk about the good,

03:17:04.380 --> 03:17:07.900
the tax reduction leads to the effect

03:17:07.910 --> 03:17:09.440
of a tax multiplier.

03:17:11.590 --> 03:17:16.090
And this effect means that with

03:17:16.100 --> 03:17:19.650
some tax cuts, the combined

03:17:19.660 --> 03:17:22.090
demand and national income

03:17:22.100 --> 03:17:24.390
will eventually grow by a

03:17:24.400 --> 03:17:26.150
larger amount.

