So, ladies and gentlemen, let us go to

03:27:51.030 --> 03:27:53.700
the last topic of our course with you.

03:27:55.660 --> 03:27:58.080
Money, banks and monetary policy.

03:27:59.160 --> 03:28:00.180
Please see the topic on

03:28:00.190 --> 03:28:02.900
the slide.

03:28:03.560 --> 03:28:07.900
The first is money and money aggregates.

03:28:11.750 --> 03:28:13.930
The first thing I would

03:28:13.940 --> 03:28:15.970
like to point out is that

03:28:16.570 --> 03:28:19.490
it is wrong to claim money

03:28:19.500 --> 03:28:22.010
with the notes we carry in

03:28:22.020 --> 03:28:23.210
our wallets.

03:28:23.810 --> 03:28:26.510
It is money, but it is not the

03:28:26.520 --> 03:28:28.470
only possible form of money.

03:28:30.210 --> 03:28:32.170
This is a strict definition of money.

03:28:32.830 --> 03:28:34.630
Please see the slide.

03:28:35.070 --> 03:28:38.130
Money is any good that

03:28:38.470 --> 03:28:40.870
can perform three functions.

03:28:43.070 --> 03:28:45.930
The first function is the means of handling.

03:28:48.630 --> 03:28:51.150
The second function is the

03:28:51.160 --> 03:28:52.370
measurement of value.

03:28:52.910 --> 03:28:55.010
The third function is the means of storage.

03:28:56.190 --> 03:28:57.970
What do these functions mean?

03:28:58.770 --> 03:29:00.810
Many of you have probably heard

03:29:00.820 --> 03:29:01.870
of it.

03:29:02.570 --> 03:29:04.590
The means of circulation means

03:29:04.600 --> 03:29:07.550
that goods are exchanged through money.

03:29:08.210 --> 03:29:10.530
If there were no money, how would

03:29:10.540 --> 03:29:11.650
we have to exchange?

03:29:12.330 --> 03:29:15.970
Probably a goods.

03:29:16.350 --> 03:29:17.930
In the Barter.

03:29:18.630 --> 03:29:21.110
In principle, exchange is possible, but

03:29:21.120 --> 03:29:23.070
it is very difficult.

03:29:23.210 --> 03:29:25.250
The use of money as a means of

03:29:25.260 --> 03:29:27.450
circulation often simplifies

03:29:27.460 --> 03:29:28.650
the exchange.

03:29:29.010 --> 03:29:31.430
In this sense, money is no less

03:29:31.440 --> 03:29:32.710
a great invention of mankind

03:29:32.720 --> 03:29:34.670
than the wheel.

03:29:36.670 --> 03:29:38.230
The second function is the

03:29:38.240 --> 03:29:39.750
measurement of value.

03:29:39.890 --> 03:29:43.890
The value of all goods is expressed

03:29:43.900 --> 03:29:45.470
in money.

03:29:45.630 --> 03:29:47.570
Again, if there were no money, it

03:29:47.910 --> 03:29:49.150
would be hard to say, for example,

03:29:49.160 --> 03:29:51.530
how much a suit costs.

03:29:51.770 --> 03:29:53.650
So many shirts, or so many

03:29:53.660 --> 03:29:55.490
shoes, or so many shorts,

03:29:55.500 --> 03:29:56.770
and so on.

03:29:58.030 --> 03:29:59.410
There would be no single meter.

03:30:00.490 --> 03:30:03.670
Money allows us to bring everything

03:30:03.680 --> 03:30:06.050
to one measurement – all commodities.

03:30:06.550 --> 03:30:08.650
And finally, the third function is

03:30:08.660 --> 03:30:09.930
the means of storage.

03:30:10.310 --> 03:30:13.970
It means that money performs the

03:30:13.980 --> 03:30:15.430
function when it is not spent immediately

03:30:15.440 --> 03:30:17.330
upon receipt, but is

03:30:17.340 --> 03:30:19.450
saved for further purchases.

03:30:21.670 --> 03:30:24.050
The history of humanity is the history

03:30:24.060 --> 03:30:25.110
of money.

03:30:26.970 --> 03:30:27.690
In my opinion, it is a very

03:30:27.700 --> 03:30:28.850
fascinating story.

03:30:29.490 --> 03:30:31.030
Unfortunately, there is no time

03:30:31.090 --> 03:30:33.590
to explain it in detail.

03:30:33.600 --> 03:30:35.910
Well, you probably know that historically,

03:30:35.920 --> 03:30:37.870
money has been individual commodities

03:30:37.880 --> 03:30:41.670
from the beginning.

03:30:42.230 --> 03:30:44.170
What goods are used as money?

03:30:46.000 --> 03:30:48.320
Those that were in this area are

03:30:48.640 --> 03:30:52.300
the most important, the most used.

03:30:52.860 --> 03:30:55.920
Where is the grain, where is the honey, where are

03:30:55.930 --> 03:30:56.720
the skins.

03:30:56.900 --> 03:30:58.880
The Vikings have brown fish, for example.

03:31:02.380 --> 03:31:04.340
That is what is interesting.

03:31:06.020 --> 03:31:08.400
These were so-called commodity

03:31:11.880 --> 03:31:13.650
money, but there were also

03:31:13.660 --> 03:31:15.650
so-called symbolic money.

03:31:19.120 --> 03:31:21.280
Symbolic money, the role

03:31:21.290 --> 03:31:23.800
of symbolic money performed

03:31:23.810 --> 03:31:27.460
a good that could not be used.

03:31:27.780 --> 03:31:29.780
Not for production or consumption.

03:31:30.040 --> 03:31:31.240
What objects are.

03:31:33.400 --> 03:31:35.860
Where they were shells of some particular

03:31:35.870 --> 03:31:39.320
shape, where they were dog teeth.

03:31:39.580 --> 03:31:41.920
On the island of Yab in the Pacific

03:31:42.140 --> 03:31:44.660
Ocean, money was stones with holes

03:31:44.670 --> 03:31:46.760
in the middle, which was convenient

03:31:46.770 --> 03:31:48.440
to wear on the six.

03:31:48.620 --> 03:31:50.480
The heavier the stone, the greater

03:31:50.490 --> 03:31:52.880
the value in exchange it represented.

03:31:55.280 --> 03:31:56.680
That is, symbolic money,

03:31:56.840 --> 03:31:58.240
some items that are

03:31:58.250 --> 03:32:00.260
used as money, but which

03:32:00.270 --> 03:32:02.000
can not be used otherwise.

03:32:02.010 --> 03:32:04.360
Not for production, not for consumption.

03:32:05.160 --> 03:32:06.760
But the existence of symbolic

03:32:06.770 --> 03:32:09.760
money suggests that

03:32:09.770 --> 03:32:12.260
money can be any good that

03:32:12.270 --> 03:32:14.780
people agree to

03:32:14.790 --> 03:32:17.120
consider money.

03:32:18.080 --> 03:32:19.880
Money is a matter of convention.

03:32:20.420 --> 03:32:22.660
The only thing that is required is

03:32:22.670 --> 03:32:24.740
that this benefit is in limited quantity.

03:32:25.040 --> 03:32:26.420
No one will give real goods for

03:32:26.430 --> 03:32:28.000
something that rolls freely

03:32:28.010 --> 03:32:29.300
under his feet.

03:32:31.140 --> 03:32:33.120
Very often, the use of a particular

03:32:33.130 --> 03:32:34.360
object as symbolic money

03:32:34.370 --> 03:32:36.560
is consumed by the authority

03:32:36.570 --> 03:32:39.040
of the state, which obliges

03:32:39.050 --> 03:32:40.740
the object to pay, and it

03:32:40.750 --> 03:32:42.920
itself accepts it to

03:32:42.930 --> 03:32:43.860
pay taxes.

03:32:44.500 --> 03:32:46.240
But, for example, our paper

03:32:46.250 --> 03:32:48.620
money is nothing but

03:32:48.630 --> 03:32:50.380
symbolic money.

03:32:50.960 --> 03:32:54.480
Because for a thousand ruble

03:32:54.490 --> 03:32:56.460
note you can get much more goods

03:32:56.470 --> 03:32:59.960
in exchange than for a piece of

03:32:59.970 --> 03:33:03.820
paper of the same area.

03:33:06.990 --> 03:33:10.950
How did the history of money develop?

03:33:12.470 --> 03:33:14.770
The role of money has gradually been fixed,

03:33:14.790 --> 03:33:16.790
as you know, behind the precious metals.

03:33:17.270 --> 03:33:18.810
In Europe, silver was first

03:33:18.820 --> 03:33:20.310
money, gold was too little,

03:33:20.320 --> 03:33:22.290
and then gold.

03:33:23.870 --> 03:33:27.170
And then, gradually, gold

03:33:27.180 --> 03:33:30.550
and silver were replaced by

03:33:30.560 --> 03:33:31.950
paper money.

03:33:33.010 --> 03:33:35.410
What is paper money?

03:33:36.730 --> 03:33:39.590
These are actually bank

03:33:39.600 --> 03:33:41.030
debt receipts.

03:33:42.390 --> 03:33:43.890
What did banks do?

03:33:44.930 --> 03:33:47.150
They accepted gold and silver

03:33:47.160 --> 03:33:49.710
in deposits, and instead gave their

03:33:49.720 --> 03:33:51.410
debt receipts to depositors, banknotes

03:33:51.420 --> 03:33:53.630
that depositors used

03:33:53.640 --> 03:33:55.190
for transactions.

03:33:55.570 --> 03:33:57.910
Banks were obliged to exchange

03:33:57.920 --> 03:34:00.690
banknotes for coins at the first request.

03:34:04.270 --> 03:34:06.990
And gradually the world of

03:34:07.000 --> 03:34:09.850
banks emerged the largest banks,

03:34:09.910 --> 03:34:11.430
central banks.

03:34:13.910 --> 03:34:16.150
And they also took gold and silver

03:34:18.080 --> 03:34:20.250
in deposits, and issued their

03:34:20.260 --> 03:34:23.350
receipts, national paper money.

03:34:25.870 --> 03:34:28.450
The modern paper money

03:34:28.590 --> 03:34:30.810
we are used to is nothing

03:34:30.820 --> 03:34:33.790
more than central bank

03:34:33.800 --> 03:34:35.010
debt receipts.

03:34:37.340 --> 03:34:41.130
But if debt receipts, then immediately

03:34:41.140 --> 03:34:44.690
the question arises of receipt

03:34:44.700 --> 03:34:45.570
for what?

03:34:47.400 --> 03:34:48.840
There was no problem before.

03:34:49.220 --> 03:34:52.640
Central banks were obliged to

03:34:52.650 --> 03:34:55.800
exchange their banknotes, their

03:34:55.810 --> 03:34:58.400
debt receipts, for gold, for example.

03:35:01.110 --> 03:35:03.120
What is bad about this system?

03:35:05.100 --> 03:35:07.300
If paper money is tied to gold,

03:35:07.310 --> 03:35:10.300
then its quantity in the economy

03:35:10.310 --> 03:35:12.520
must correspond to the amount

03:35:12.530 --> 03:35:14.460
of gold in the bank's deposits.

03:35:19.790 --> 03:35:21.290
Imagine that the amount of gold

03:35:21.300 --> 03:35:22.990
in the economy has decreased.

03:35:24.860 --> 03:35:25.920
What will it lead to?

03:35:26.740 --> 03:35:29.200
Paper money will be less.

03:35:32.560 --> 03:35:35.060
Prices will fall, but if the money

03:35:35.070 --> 03:35:37.940
is less, the prices will become less.

03:35:39.420 --> 03:35:40.820
If gold, on the contrary, came into

03:35:40.830 --> 03:35:42.140
the economy, paper money will

03:35:42.150 --> 03:35:44.740
become more, prices will rise.

03:35:46.990 --> 03:35:48.870
But in general, the price jump, even

03:35:48.880 --> 03:35:51.310
up or down, is harmful to the economy.

03:35:52.430 --> 03:35:52.810
Why is?

03:35:53.510 --> 03:35:54.890
Business needs stability.

03:35:55.450 --> 03:35:57.730
Price jumping increases business

03:35:57.740 --> 03:35:59.790
risks, respectively, negatively affect

03:35:59.800 --> 03:36:01.270
the development of the economy.

03:36:02.800 --> 03:36:05.160
In the era of gold standards,

03:36:05.170 --> 03:36:08.240
price hikes could not be avoided.

03:36:08.860 --> 03:36:11.000
A year with high prices could well

03:36:11.010 --> 03:36:12.980
follow a year with low prices.

03:36:13.260 --> 03:36:14.620
Gold came into the economy,

03:36:14.940 --> 03:36:16.560
paper money became more, and prices

03:36:17.360 --> 03:36:19.340
increased accordingly.

03:36:19.540 --> 03:36:21.360
Gold has gone out of the economy, money has

03:36:21.370 --> 03:36:23.420
become less, prices will fall.

03:36:27.940 --> 03:36:28.220
So that it won't be boring,

03:36:28.230 --> 03:36:31.260
I'll tell you a story.

03:36:36.110 --> 03:36:39.270
The United States of America

03:36:39.280 --> 03:36:43.190
in the 90s is now the 19th century.

03:36:43.790 --> 03:36:45.470
In circulation already then were

03:36:47.030 --> 03:36:49.740
paper dollars, but they were subject to

03:36:49.750 --> 03:36:52.200
exchange for gold.

03:36:53.670 --> 03:36:55.390
The amount of dollars in the

03:36:55.400 --> 03:36:57.490
economy should correspond

03:36:57.500 --> 03:36:59.210
to the amount of gold.

03:37:00.770 --> 03:37:02.830
As it went, the fields were

03:37:02.840 --> 03:37:05.130
exhausted, the gold in the economy

03:37:05.140 --> 03:37:05.990
became less.

03:37:08.380 --> 03:37:09.360
Prices have fallen.

03:37:11.070 --> 03:37:12.910
I have already told you that price jumping

03:37:12.920 --> 03:37:13.830
up or down is harmful to

03:37:13.840 --> 03:37:14.650
the economy.

03:37:15.450 --> 03:37:18.030
But when prices fall, there is another

03:37:18.040 --> 03:37:18.610
nuance.

03:37:20.830 --> 03:37:22.170
What do you think when prices

03:37:22.180 --> 03:37:24.410
suddenly fall, who wins, the debtor

03:37:24.470 --> 03:37:25.810
or the lender?

03:37:32.450 --> 03:37:35.990
The creditor actually wins.

03:37:36.250 --> 03:37:38.470
Well, imagine you borrowed

03:37:38.480 --> 03:37:41.790
some amount of money, you plan

03:37:41.800 --> 03:37:44.310
to produce some goods, for

03:37:44.320 --> 03:37:46.910
example, grow the harvest and

03:37:46.920 --> 03:37:50.010
settle with your lender and

03:37:50.020 --> 03:37:51.210
pay interest.

03:37:51.410 --> 03:37:54.450
And prices suddenly fell.

03:37:54.690 --> 03:37:59.650
You borrowed cheap money, and you have

03:37:59.660 --> 03:38:00.970
to give expensive money.

03:38:01.510 --> 03:38:03.250
You will have to do what?

03:38:06.430 --> 03:38:09.950
Give more goods, prices have

03:38:09.960 --> 03:38:11.950
fallen for goods to

03:38:11.960 --> 03:38:15.030
settle with your lender.

03:38:16.780 --> 03:38:19.590
This was exactly what happened in the 1990s

03:38:19.600 --> 03:38:21.170
in the United States.

03:38:21.430 --> 03:38:22.310
Prices have fallen.

03:38:22.750 --> 03:38:24.450
In a difficult situation was

03:38:24.460 --> 03:38:26.350
the real sector, which took

03:38:26.360 --> 03:38:28.270
money, which took money borrowed

03:38:28.280 --> 03:38:30.190
at a fixed interest rate.

03:38:32.850 --> 03:38:34.230
In a relatively good position were

03:38:34.240 --> 03:38:37.150
banks, which gave money in loan

03:38:37.160 --> 03:38:41.030
with cheap money, and received

03:38:41.040 --> 03:38:41.950
expensive money.

