The preparation of monetary aggregates

03:48:27.660 --> 03:48:29.490
is the prerogative of central banks.

03:48:30.370 --> 03:48:32.090
Since market economies in different

03:48:32.100 --> 03:48:34.710
countries are roughly similar, aggregates

03:48:34.720 --> 03:48:36.790
are similar.

03:48:37.050 --> 03:48:38.130
Although there is a certain difference,

03:48:38.140 --> 03:48:38.850
of course.

03:48:39.810 --> 03:48:42.590
We will talk about the money aggregates

03:48:42.600 --> 03:48:43.690
in Russia.

03:48:45.790 --> 03:48:46.910
Here, please, look at the table

03:48:47.070 --> 03:48:50.170
of the currency aggregates in Russia

03:48:50.180 --> 03:48:54.030
and their sizes for April 1, 2007.

03:48:56.320 --> 03:48:59.320
The first unit that the Bank of Russia

03:48:59.330 --> 03:49:02.460
allocates is called M0.

03:49:04.220 --> 03:49:06.880
M0 is cash in circulation

03:49:06.890 --> 03:49:09.300
or money outside the

03:49:09.310 --> 03:49:11.080
banking system.

03:49:11.090 --> 03:49:13.500
Money in the hands of households

03:49:13.510 --> 03:49:17.500
or in the companies.

03:49:17.960 --> 03:49:22.960
The next unit is called M1.

03:49:23.600 --> 03:49:25.440
Pay attention to how the aggregates

03:49:25.450 --> 03:49:26.800
are built.

03:49:28.040 --> 03:49:31.260
This is a sort of snow

03:49:31.270 --> 03:49:33.740
coma principle.

03:49:34.260 --> 03:49:37.240
Each next unit includes the

03:49:37.250 --> 03:49:40.120
previous plus something else.

03:49:40.130 --> 03:49:42.500
Each next unit is a broader

03:49:42.510 --> 03:49:45.260
concept than the previous one.

03:49:46.760 --> 03:49:49.900
And the M1 unit actually includes

03:49:49.910 --> 03:49:50.580
what?

03:49:52.020 --> 03:49:54.160
First, M0, cash, plus funds

03:49:56.520 --> 03:49:59.060
on deposits for demand,

03:49:59.070 --> 03:50:01.940
plus funds on current

03:50:01.950 --> 03:50:04.640
billing accounts.

03:50:06.000 --> 03:50:10.480
The next unit is called M2 and

03:50:10.490 --> 03:50:13.040
includes, as you already

03:50:13.050 --> 03:50:17.060
understand, the unit M1 plus

03:50:17.080 --> 03:50:19.080
funds on urgent savings

03:50:19.090 --> 03:50:21.240
deposits.

03:50:22.260 --> 03:50:24.700
The last unit used

03:50:24.710 --> 03:50:27.800
in Russia is the

03:50:27.810 --> 03:50:30.800
M3.

03:50:30.810 --> 03:50:34.450
It includes, as you can see from the

03:50:34.460 --> 03:50:37.510
table, the M2 aggregate,

03:50:37.520 --> 03:50:39.670
plus deposit sortings, plus

03:50:39.680 --> 03:50:46.050
government bonds, plus all foreign

03:50:46.060 --> 03:50:50.470
currency deposits in ruble equivalent.

03:50:50.810 --> 03:50:53.210
Note, the Central Bank of Russia

03:50:53.220 --> 03:50:55.430
reasoning about like spouses

03:50:55.440 --> 03:50:56.730
in the kitchen.

03:50:57.090 --> 03:50:58.470
They wondered, they thought about how

03:50:58.570 --> 03:50:59.350
much money they had.

03:50:59.360 --> 03:51:00.930
First remembered what?

03:51:01.710 --> 03:51:03.090
How much cash do they have?

03:51:03.430 --> 03:51:04.790
This is the M0.

03:51:05.090 --> 03:51:07.650
Then they remembered how much they have in

03:51:07.660 --> 03:51:08.970
the average current account, this is

03:51:08.980 --> 03:51:10.230
the M1 unit.

03:51:10.390 --> 03:51:12.070
Then they remembered how much money

03:51:12.080 --> 03:51:14.750
they had on an urgent savings deposit.

03:51:14.850 --> 03:51:18.110
This is the M2 unit and so on.

03:51:19.370 --> 03:51:22.070
The only thing that differentiates

03:51:22.080 --> 03:51:24.890
the mentality of the bank of

03:51:24.900 --> 03:51:27.230
Russia from the mentality of the spouses

03:51:27.240 --> 03:51:29.690
in the kitchen is that the spouses

03:51:29.700 --> 03:51:32.770
would probably very quickly remember

03:51:32.780 --> 03:51:36.450
their cash currency, dollars or euros.

03:51:37.430 --> 03:51:40.570
But the Bank of Russia, the cash

03:51:40.580 --> 03:51:42.930
currency available in the hands of

03:51:42.940 --> 03:51:47.410
the population, does not include in any unit.

03:51:47.910 --> 03:51:50.310
Includes currency deposits,

03:51:50.320 --> 03:51:53.170
currency accounts in banks

03:51:53.390 --> 03:51:56.490
and cash in no single unit.

03:51:56.570 --> 03:52:00.670
I would like to point out that the money

03:52:00.680 --> 03:52:04.410
aggregates are arranged on the principle

03:52:04.420 --> 03:52:06.950
of decreasing liquidity.

03:52:08.690 --> 03:52:12.090
Each subsequent aggregate includes

03:52:12.100 --> 03:52:14.630
all, less and less liquid assets.

03:52:16.810 --> 03:52:20.090
The most liquid unit M0.

03:52:23.730 --> 03:52:26.910
The lowest liquid assets are in the

03:52:26.920 --> 03:52:28.890
M3 aggregate.

03:52:29.230 --> 03:52:32.770
Liquidity is the ability of

03:52:32.780 --> 03:52:35.170
an asset, quickly and without

03:52:35.180 --> 03:52:38.270
loss, to exchange for other assets.

