time of buying gold, currency

03:55:49.950 --> 03:55:51.360
and securities.

03:55:51.820 --> 03:55:53.580
They are simulated, cash arises

03:55:53.590 --> 03:55:55.440
in circulation later.

03:55:55.450 --> 03:55:58.360
But anyway, when the central

03:56:00.180 --> 03:56:03.950
bank buys gold, currency or

03:56:03.960 --> 03:56:06.890
securities, the cash supply

03:56:06.900 --> 03:56:09.370
in the economy increases.

03:56:09.990 --> 03:56:11.310
But for the sake of simplicity, it

03:56:11.410 --> 03:56:12.110
can be assumed that it

03:56:12.120 --> 03:56:13.910
is paid directly in cash,

03:56:13.920 --> 03:56:15.650
although this is not certain.

03:56:18.110 --> 03:56:19.290
Logic is probably understandable.

03:56:20.030 --> 03:56:23.130
I am a central bank, I buy,

03:56:23.140 --> 03:56:25.490
say, gold or government

03:56:25.500 --> 03:56:26.990
securities or U.S. dollars.

03:56:27.000 --> 03:56:27.850


03:56:28.550 --> 03:56:34.130
When I buy them, I

03:56:34.140 --> 03:56:35.690
issue cash, I pay in

03:56:35.700 --> 03:56:37.330
cash, cash, and

03:56:37.340 --> 03:56:40.090
there is a cash issue.

03:56:41.030 --> 03:56:44.210
On the other hand, cash arises in the

03:56:44.220 --> 03:56:47.970
economy as a result of the fact that

03:56:47.980 --> 03:56:50.330
the central bank lends credit

03:56:50.340 --> 03:56:53.790
to the government and commercial

03:56:53.800 --> 03:56:54.850
banks.

03:56:57.370 --> 03:56:59.370
The Central Bank does not lend

03:56:59.380 --> 03:57:01.430
individuals and firms, it lends

03:57:01.440 --> 03:57:04.110
to commercial banks and the government.

03:57:06.670 --> 03:57:08.710
Well, again, with a considerable

03:57:08.720 --> 03:57:11.510
amount of simplification, it can be

03:57:11.520 --> 03:57:14.150
assumed that the central bank issues

03:57:14.160 --> 03:57:16.010
loans in cash.

03:57:16.270 --> 03:57:19.770
Cash in circulation plus the funds

03:57:19.780 --> 03:57:22.530
of commercial banks on the Central

03:57:22.540 --> 03:57:24.610
Bank accounts form

03:57:24.620 --> 03:57:27.870
the monetary base.

03:57:30.050 --> 03:57:33.790
The monetary base is a kind of skeleton

03:57:33.800 --> 03:57:36.970
of the money mass, a kind of primacy of

03:57:36.980 --> 03:57:38.290
the money mass.

03:57:39.680 --> 03:57:41.820
The money mass in the economy

03:57:41.830 --> 03:57:44.460
grows from the monetary base.

03:57:46.940 --> 03:57:49.120
I just want to emphasize here

03:57:49.840 --> 03:57:53.200
that the cash mass is not

03:57:53.210 --> 03:57:54.240
all cash.

03:57:55.240 --> 03:57:57.240
But you remember that there are

03:57:57.250 --> 03:57:58.540
different money aggregates.

03:57:59.120 --> 03:58:00.960
Cash is only the M0 unit, but

03:58:00.970 --> 03:58:04.400
also the M1, M2, M3 units.

03:58:07.750 --> 03:58:11.410
But still the monetary base is the basis

03:58:11.420 --> 03:58:14.390
of the monetary mass in the economy.

03:58:17.160 --> 03:58:21.060
The central bank creates the monetary base.

03:58:22.900 --> 03:58:25.300
But what is interesting is that

03:58:27.050 --> 03:58:29.520
commercial banks in the process

03:58:29.530 --> 03:58:32.440
of their activities, by issuing

03:58:32.450 --> 03:58:35.500
loans, increase the money mass

03:58:35.510 --> 03:58:36.560
in the economy.

03:58:39.790 --> 03:58:40.810
How does it happen?

03:58:42.530 --> 03:58:44.730
Well, imagine that you or your

03:58:44.740 --> 03:58:47.390
company came to a commercial bank

03:58:47.400 --> 03:58:49.090
for a loan.

03:58:49.610 --> 03:58:51.710
How will a commercial bank give you a loan?

03:58:53.110 --> 03:58:56.910
Most often, you open an account.

03:59:03.800 --> 03:59:07.560
But as you hope to remember, the current

03:59:08.200 --> 03:59:12.560
accounts of firms and the population

03:59:12.570 --> 03:59:14.760
in commercial banks, it is also

03:59:14.770 --> 03:59:17.560
money, it is the M1 unit.

03:59:17.780 --> 03:59:20.700
Accordingly, issuing loans by opening

03:59:20.710 --> 03:59:22.500
accounts, commercial banks

03:59:22.800 --> 03:59:25.840
create additional money in the

03:59:25.850 --> 03:59:28.540
form of an aggregate, in the form

03:59:28.550 --> 03:59:30.800
of current accounts, that is, in the

03:59:30.840 --> 03:59:33.260
form of an aggregate M1.

03:59:35.320 --> 03:59:36.860
How is it done?

03:59:38.020 --> 03:59:40.020
Here you better look at this mechanism

03:59:40.030 --> 03:59:42.520
in detail on the texts of lectures,

03:59:42.530 --> 03:59:45.240
on the text of lectures.

03:59:45.760 --> 03:59:47.360
It is detailed there.

03:59:50.500 --> 03:59:53.080
And we will immediately move

03:59:53.090 --> 03:59:57.260
to another very important issue, monetary

03:59:57.860 --> 04:00:03.080
policy and its instruments.

04:00:03.090 --> 04:00:06.460
Read the definition,

04:00:07.140 --> 04:00:09.000
see the slide.

04:00:09.500 --> 04:00:12.340
Monetary or monetary policy is

04:00:12.350 --> 04:00:15.420
a policy on changing the

04:00:15.430 --> 04:00:18.880
monetary mass in the economy.

04:00:20.340 --> 04:00:22.900
The central bank plays an important

04:00:22.910 --> 04:00:25.760
role in its implementation as the

04:00:25.770 --> 04:00:28.840
main link of the country's banking system.

04:00:32.410 --> 04:00:35.850
Let us look at the central bank'

04:00:35.860 --> 04:00:38.090
s main functions.

04:00:38.430 --> 04:00:39.970
Look at the slide.

04:00:43.420 --> 04:00:46.560
The central bank is the

04:00:46.570 --> 04:00:50.980
country's emission center.

04:00:51.060 --> 04:00:53.840
That is, it monopolyly releases

04:00:53.850 --> 04:00:56.900
national banknotes in circulation.

04:00:56.910 --> 04:00:58.060


04:00:59.830 --> 04:01:04.050
The second function is that the Central Bank

04:01:04.060 --> 04:01:05.630
is a bank of banks.

04:01:06.250 --> 04:01:08.010
What does it express?

04:01:09.070 --> 04:01:11.690
It keeps the reserves of commercial banks,

04:01:11.700 --> 04:01:15.290
issues them to courts, and there

04:01:15.300 --> 04:01:17.690
is supervision over their activities.

04:01:20.650 --> 04:01:23.730
The third most important function of the Central

04:01:23.740 --> 04:01:26.810
Bank is that it is the banking officer of the government.

04:01:27.710 --> 04:01:28.990
What does it express?

04:01:29.770 --> 04:01:32.450
The central bank places state

04:01:32.460 --> 04:01:35.330
securities, provides credit to

04:01:35.340 --> 04:01:36.970
the government, performs

04:01:36.980 --> 04:01:40.570
settlement operations for the government,

04:01:40.580 --> 04:01:43.210
keeps the Treasury accounts,

04:01:43.220 --> 04:01:45.730
and keeps official gold

04:01:45.740 --> 04:01:48.330
and currency reserves.

04:01:50.770 --> 04:01:54.970
The Central Bank is the main settlement

04:01:54.980 --> 04:01:58.270
center of the country, that

04:01:58.280 --> 04:02:01.190
is, acts as an intermediary between

04:02:01.200 --> 04:02:03.910
banks in the implementation

04:02:03.920 --> 04:02:05.950
of non-cash payments.

04:02:10.550 --> 04:02:13.320
And finally, the fifth function,

04:02:13.330 --> 04:02:14.260
which we will actually talk

04:02:14.270 --> 04:02:15.160
about later.

04:02:16.120 --> 04:02:18.780
The central bank is the body of

04:02:18.790 --> 04:02:20.740
regulation of the economy

04:02:20.750 --> 04:02:23.280
through monetary policy.

04:02:24.940 --> 04:02:26.960
Please see the following slide.

04:02:29.130 --> 04:02:32.330
It focuses on the objectives and instruments

04:02:32.340 --> 04:02:33.530
of monetary policy.

04:02:35.250 --> 04:02:37.070
There are strategic goals, there are

04:02:37.080 --> 04:02:38.330
intermediate goals.

04:02:38.590 --> 04:02:40.250
I will speak about the strategic

04:02:40.260 --> 04:02:43.070
goals, the ultimate goals, the goals

04:02:43.170 --> 04:02:44.650
of the Central Bank.

04:02:45.010 --> 04:02:48.210
What does the central bank want?

04:02:48.550 --> 04:02:49.830
What are its strategic goals?

04:02:49.950 --> 04:02:51.610
Look at the slide.

04:02:52.010 --> 04:02:54.770
The first goal is economic growth.

04:02:56.270 --> 04:02:58.110
He wants the economy to grow.

04:03:00.320 --> 04:03:03.120
The second is full employment.

04:03:06.900 --> 04:03:09.320
Unemployment should not exceed

04:03:09.330 --> 04:03:13.060
the minimum required level.

04:03:16.680 --> 04:03:21.110
The third key is price

04:03:21.120 --> 04:03:22.050
stability.

04:03:24.110 --> 04:03:28.170
The fourth feature is a stable balance

04:03:28.180 --> 04:03:29.190
of payments.

04:03:31.480 --> 04:03:34.960
To these objectives, the Bank

04:03:34.970 --> 04:03:37.120
of Russia may use the following

04:03:37.130 --> 04:03:40.900
basic instruments.

04:03:44.080 --> 04:03:46.100
Look at the slide.

04:03:46.480 --> 04:03:50.220
Let's not rush to find out the tools.

04:03:57.810 --> 04:04:01.210
The first instrument is the purchase and

04:04:01.220 --> 04:04:03.410
sale of government securities.

04:04:08.870 --> 04:04:12.840
Or, as they say, operations in the

04:04:12.850 --> 04:04:13.840
open market.

04:04:17.590 --> 04:04:19.210
How can the central bank regulate

04:04:19.220 --> 04:04:22.590
the money supply by using

04:04:22.600 --> 04:04:25.890
this function, by using this

04:04:25.900 --> 04:04:27.130
instrument?

04:04:29.200 --> 04:04:31.640
Well, imagine, I am the

04:04:31.650 --> 04:04:33.100
central bank and you are

04:04:33.110 --> 04:04:35.120
commercial banks.

04:04:36.720 --> 04:04:39.880
Let's say I buy your

04:04:41.330 --> 04:04:43.250
government securities

04:04:43.260 --> 04:04:45.150
in the balance sheet.

04:04:49.300 --> 04:04:52.920
When I buy these papers,

04:04:52.930 --> 04:04:55.000
I pay in rubles.

04:04:55.000 --> 04:05:03.870
That is, I increase the monetary base and

04:05:03.880 --> 04:05:05.730
the money mass in the economy.

04:05:05.990 --> 04:05:07.190
But it can be imagined.

04:05:07.410 --> 04:05:08.950
You are commercial banks, you are

04:05:08.960 --> 04:05:12.370
my securities, and I am the answer to you.

04:05:13.190 --> 04:05:16.110
So, by buying securities, I increase

04:05:16.120 --> 04:05:18.110
the money mass.

04:05:23.320 --> 04:05:26.380
Most often in modern conditions, the

04:05:26.390 --> 04:05:29.140
Bank of Russia carries out operations

04:05:29.150 --> 04:05:32.420
in the open market through direct

04:05:32.430 --> 04:05:36.300
and reverse repo transactions.

04:05:39.260 --> 04:05:40.280
What is it?

04:05:43.620 --> 04:05:46.940
Repo operations, in general,

04:05:47.240 --> 04:05:51.020
are repurchase operations.

04:05:52.730 --> 04:05:56.910
Suppose commercial banks have

04:05:56.920 --> 04:05:59.090
securities.

04:06:00.570 --> 04:06:02.810
They are temporarily sold

04:06:02.820 --> 04:06:04.530
to the central bank.

04:06:05.610 --> 04:06:07.890
The central bank pays in rubles

04:06:07.900 --> 04:06:11.270
and thus increases the money

04:06:11.280 --> 04:06:13.030
mass in the economy.

04:06:14.570 --> 04:06:19.050
But the REPO deal implies that

04:06:19.060 --> 04:06:21.370
after a certain time commercial

04:06:21.380 --> 04:06:26.150
banks are obliged to buy these

04:06:26.160 --> 04:06:28.890
securities back from the

04:06:31.600 --> 04:06:34.210
Central Bank at a higher

04:06:34.220 --> 04:06:35.310
price.

04:06:35.930 --> 04:06:38.530
The price difference is the percentage

04:06:38.540 --> 04:06:40.790
that the central bank

04:06:40.800 --> 04:06:42.850
receives from commercial banks.

04:06:42.860 --> 04:06:46.400
But still, with the associative operation

04:06:46.410 --> 04:06:49.480
of direct REPO, the Central Bank

04:06:49.490 --> 04:06:51.680
increases the money mass in the economy.

04:06:53.420 --> 04:06:55.780
And with the reverse REPO operation, everything

04:06:55.790 --> 04:06:57.020
happens the opposite.

04:06:57.520 --> 04:07:01.420
The central bank temporarily

04:07:01.430 --> 04:07:03.400
sells its state securities

04:07:03.410 --> 04:07:05.400
to commercial banks.

04:07:06.640 --> 04:07:09.160
And when he sells them, he temporarily

04:07:09.170 --> 04:07:11.460
pulls the money out of the

04:07:11.470 --> 04:07:14.340
economy, reduces the money out.

04:07:18.330 --> 04:07:20.610
The second instrument of purchase is the sale

04:07:20.620 --> 04:07:22.430
of foreign currency.

04:07:25.080 --> 04:07:27.440
But here is essentially the same mechanism.

04:07:30.250 --> 04:07:32.350
If the central bank buys dollars

04:07:32.360 --> 04:07:35.350
or euros, it emits rubles

04:07:35.360 --> 04:07:36.810
in response.

04:07:40.100 --> 04:07:41.720
As a result, the money mass in the

04:07:41.730 --> 04:07:42.920
economy is increasing.

04:07:43.440 --> 04:07:45.040
Well, imagine, I am the Central Bank, you

04:07:45.050 --> 04:07:46.220
are a commercial bank, you sell me currency,

04:07:46.230 --> 04:07:48.200
you give me currency, I give you

04:07:48.210 --> 04:07:49.620
rubles.

04:07:49.900 --> 04:07:52.080
As a result, the money mass

04:07:52.090 --> 04:07:52.740
is increasing.

04:07:54.500 --> 04:07:58.180
On the contrary, when the central bank

04:08:00.460 --> 04:08:02.160
sells currency to commercial

04:08:05.210 --> 04:08:07.120
banks, it pulls rubles out of

04:08:08.930 --> 04:08:12.000
the economy, that is, the money mass decreases.

04:08:14.120 --> 04:08:17.620
The third instrument is the change

04:08:19.780 --> 04:08:22.500
of the mandatory reserve rate.

04:08:28.360 --> 04:08:30.680
What is a compulsory reserve standard?

04:08:33.050 --> 04:08:35.730
Let's say commercial banks

04:08:35.740 --> 04:08:39.750
are attracting funds from depositors.

04:08:39.760 --> 04:08:42.530
They cannot all these attracted funds

04:08:42.540 --> 04:08:44.490
to let business turnaround.

04:08:44.810 --> 04:08:46.910
For example, allow for loans.

04:08:50.750 --> 04:08:54.990
They are obliged to reserve part

04:08:55.000 --> 04:08:57.230
of the funds attracted at

04:08:57.240 --> 04:08:58.490
the Central Bank.

04:08:59.790 --> 04:09:03.090
Accordingly, the higher the

04:09:03.100 --> 04:09:06.690
mandatory reserve rate, the

04:09:06.700 --> 04:09:09.730
less the commercial banks

04:09:09.740 --> 04:09:11.810
have funds to issue loans.

04:09:13.600 --> 04:09:16.160
And I have already told you that all

04:09:16.170 --> 04:09:17.780
kinds of expenses commercial banks give

04:09:17.790 --> 04:09:19.780
out loans, opening current accounts

04:09:19.790 --> 04:09:22.260
to borrowers, they increase the

04:09:22.270 --> 04:09:23.340
money mass in the economy.

04:09:25.140 --> 04:09:26.820
The higher the mandatory reserve

04:09:26.830 --> 04:09:29.160
rate, the less the money

04:09:29.170 --> 04:09:30.700
in the economy.

04:09:30.920 --> 04:09:31.820
And the opposite.

04:09:34.900 --> 04:09:36.060
The fourth instrument.

04:09:37.920 --> 04:09:41.680
Changes in interest rates on deposits

04:09:41.690 --> 04:09:44.080
of commercial banks in the

04:09:44.090 --> 04:09:44.840
Central Bank.

04:09:47.530 --> 04:09:48.970
How does this tool work?

04:09:49.790 --> 04:09:53.270
I have already said that commercial

04:09:53.280 --> 04:09:56.570
banks are obliged to reserve part

04:09:56.580 --> 04:09:58.350
of the funds attracted in

04:09:58.360 --> 04:09:59.290
the Central Bank.

04:10:02.100 --> 04:10:04.000
But, say, the central bank

04:10:04.010 --> 04:10:06.860
wants commercial banks to hold

04:10:06.870 --> 04:10:09.020
more money in the

04:10:09.030 --> 04:10:10.280
central bank.

04:10:12.890 --> 04:10:14.750
On the one hand, can he do anything?

04:10:16.270 --> 04:10:19.010
Increase the mandatory reserve rate.

04:10:22.800 --> 04:10:24.540
However, central banks rarely

04:10:24.550 --> 04:10:26.380
use this tool.

04:10:26.390 --> 04:10:29.320
What is this tool bad?

04:10:30.100 --> 04:10:33.600
He cuts all the banks under one scarf.

04:10:34.540 --> 04:10:36.240
There is no separate reserve

04:10:36.250 --> 04:10:38.520
rate for Sberbank and no separate

04:10:38.530 --> 04:10:40.100
for Alpha Bank.

04:10:40.360 --> 04:10:41.420
She is the same for everyone.

04:10:43.490 --> 04:10:45.230
What if he doesn't want to cut them under

04:10:45.240 --> 04:10:46.010
one hammer?

04:10:46.930 --> 04:10:50.810
What can the central bank offer?

04:10:53.550 --> 04:10:55.590
He may offer commercial banks

04:10:55.600 --> 04:10:58.890
on a voluntary basis to

04:10:58.900 --> 04:11:01.830
open additional depository

04:11:01.840 --> 04:11:04.370
accounts, on which he pays

04:11:04.380 --> 04:11:05.230
interest.

04:11:06.530 --> 04:11:08.210
The central bank, the commercial

04:11:08.220 --> 04:11:09.450
bank, does not pay interest

04:11:09.460 --> 04:11:11.390
on the obligatory reserves.

04:11:11.530 --> 04:11:12.310
So throughout the world.

04:11:13.430 --> 04:11:15.450
But on deposits, which are

04:11:15.530 --> 04:11:16.550
opened on a voluntary

04:11:16.560 --> 04:11:18.790
basis, the central bank pays,

04:11:18.800 --> 04:11:20.430
even if small, but still

04:11:20.440 --> 04:11:22.590
a percentage.

04:11:26.500 --> 04:11:28.120
How much higher is this percentage?

04:11:31.030 --> 04:11:31.930
by what?

04:11:32.490 --> 04:11:34.870
The more of their funds commercial

04:11:35.150 --> 04:11:36.670
banks hold on the deposit

04:11:36.680 --> 04:11:38.690
account of the central banks.

04:11:38.790 --> 04:11:40.230
The less they can

04:11:40.240 --> 04:11:42.250
lend.

04:11:44.000 --> 04:11:45.800
And I have said that whenever

04:11:46.740 --> 04:11:47.660
commercial banks lend, they

04:11:47.670 --> 04:11:48.880
increase the money mass in

04:11:48.890 --> 04:11:49.820
the economy.

04:11:50.040 --> 04:11:51.680
The less money in the economy.

04:11:51.690 --> 04:11:52.360


04:11:54.810 --> 04:11:56.290
The fifth instrument.

04:11:57.590 --> 04:12:01.950
Changes in the accounting rate

04:12:01.960 --> 04:12:04.070
or refinancing rate.

04:12:07.060 --> 04:12:08.540
In the West, it is a very important

04:12:08.550 --> 04:12:10.880
tool for regulating the money mass

04:12:10.890 --> 04:12:12.180
in the economy.

04:12:14.090 --> 04:12:18.310
Accounting rate is the rate

04:12:18.320 --> 04:12:22.410
at which Western central banks

04:12:22.420 --> 04:12:24.310
lend commercial.

04:12:24.850 --> 04:12:26.490
Well, let them lend not at an accounting

04:12:26.500 --> 04:12:28.310
rate, but at a rate very close

04:12:28.320 --> 04:12:30.370
to the accounting rate.

04:12:32.460 --> 04:12:33.580
So what does it work out?

04:12:35.560 --> 04:12:39.740
The lower the accounting rate,

04:12:39.750 --> 04:12:42.720
the more loans commercial banks

04:12:42.730 --> 04:12:46.800
can take from the central bank,

04:12:49.800 --> 04:12:53.940
the more loans they give

04:12:56.620 --> 04:12:59.790
themselves, the more money in

04:12:59.800 --> 04:13:01.150
the economy.

04:13:01.830 --> 04:13:03.950
The accounting rate determines

04:13:03.960 --> 04:13:09.100
a lot in Western countries.

04:13:09.620 --> 04:13:13.180
If it decreases, then the interest

04:13:13.340 --> 04:13:16.160
rate in the economy also decreases.

04:13:17.970 --> 04:13:19.970
A lot depends on interest

04:13:19.980 --> 04:13:21.930
rates.

04:13:22.070 --> 04:13:24.090
And investment, and consumption, and the exchange

04:13:24.100 --> 04:13:25.810
rate of the national currency, and much more.

